39bool CompressedTextureFormatRequiresExactSize(GLenum internalFormat)
40{
41 // List of compressed format that require that the texture size is smaller than or a multiple of
42 // the compressed block size.
43 switch (internalFormat)
44 {
45 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB_S3TC_DXT1_EXT:
46 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT1_EXT:
47 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT3_ANGLE:
48 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT5_ANGLE:
49 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB_S3TC_DXT1_EXT:
50 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB_ALPHA_S3TC_DXT1_EXT:
51 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB_ALPHA_S3TC_DXT3_EXT:
52 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB_ALPHA_S3TC_DXT5_EXT:
53 case GL_ETC1_RGB8_LOSSY_DECODE_ANGLE:
54 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB8_LOSSY_DECODE_ETC2_ANGLE:
55 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB8_LOSSY_DECODE_ETC2_ANGLE:
56 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB8_PUNCHTHROUGH_ALPHA1_LOSSY_DECODE_ETC2_ANGLE:
57 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB8_PUNCHTHROUGH_ALPHA1_LOSSY_DECODE_ETC2_ANGLE:
58 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA8_LOSSY_DECODE_ETC2_EAC_ANGLE:
59 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_LOSSY_DECODE_ETC2_EAC_ANGLE:
60 case GL_COMPRESSED_RED_RGTC1_EXT:
61 case GL_COMPRESSED_SIGNED_RED_RGTC1_EXT:
62 case GL_COMPRESSED_RED_GREEN_RGTC2_EXT:
63 case GL_COMPRESSED_SIGNED_RED_GREEN_RGTC2_EXT:
64 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_BPTC_UNORM_EXT:
65 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB_ALPHA_BPTC_UNORM_EXT:
66 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB_BPTC_SIGNED_FLOAT_EXT:
67 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB_BPTC_UNSIGNED_FLOAT_EXT:
68 return true;
69
70 default:
71 return false;
72 }
73}
74bool CompressedSubTextureFormatRequiresExactSize(GLenum internalFormat)
75{
76 // Compressed sub textures have additional formats that requires exact size.
77 // ES 3.1, Section 8.7, Page 171
78 return CompressedTextureFormatRequiresExactSize(internalFormat) ||
79 IsETC2EACFormat(internalFormat);
80}
81
82bool DifferenceCanOverflow(GLint a, GLint b)
83{
84 CheckedNumeric<GLint> checkedA(a);
85 checkedA -= b;
86 // Use negation to make sure that the difference can't overflow regardless of the order.
87 checkedA = -checkedA;
88 return !checkedA.IsValid();
89}

91bool ValidReadPixelsTypeEnum(const Context *context, GLenum type)
92{
93 switch (type)
94 {
95 // Types referenced in Table 3.4 of the ES 2.0.25 spec
96 case GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE:
97 case GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT_4_4_4_4:
98 case GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT_5_5_5_1:
99 case GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT_5_6_5:
100 return context->getClientVersion() >= ES_2_0;
101
102 // Types referenced in Table 3.2 of the ES 3.0.5 spec (Except depth stencil)
103 case GL_BYTE:
104 case GL_INT:
105 case GL_SHORT:
106 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT:
107 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_10F_11F_11F_REV:
108 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_24_8:
109 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_2_10_10_10_REV:
110 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_5_9_9_9_REV:
111 case GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT:
112 case GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT_1_5_5_5_REV_EXT:
113 case GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT_4_4_4_4_REV_EXT:
114 return context->getClientVersion() >= ES_3_0;
115
116 case GL_FLOAT:
117 return context->getClientVersion() >= ES_3_0 ||
118 context->getExtensions().textureFloatOES ||
119 context->getExtensions().colorBufferHalfFloat;
120
121 case GL_HALF_FLOAT:
122 return context->getClientVersion() >= ES_3_0 ||
123 context->getExtensions().textureHalfFloat;
124
125 case GL_HALF_FLOAT_OES:
126 return context->getExtensions().colorBufferHalfFloat;
127
128 default:
129 return false;
130 }
131}
132
133bool ValidReadPixelsFormatEnum(const Context *context, GLenum format)
134{
135 switch (format)
136 {
137 // Formats referenced in Table 3.4 of the ES 2.0.25 spec (Except luminance)
138 case GL_RGBA:
139 case GL_RGB:
140 case GL_ALPHA:
141 return context->getClientVersion() >= ES_2_0;
142
143 // Formats referenced in Table 3.2 of the ES 3.0.5 spec
144 case GL_RG:
145 case GL_RED:
146 case GL_RGBA_INTEGER:
147 case GL_RGB_INTEGER:
148 case GL_RG_INTEGER:
149 case GL_RED_INTEGER:
150 return context->getClientVersion() >= ES_3_0;
151
152 case GL_SRGB_ALPHA_EXT:
153 case GL_SRGB_EXT:
154 return context->getExtensions().sRGB;
155
156 case GL_BGRA_EXT:
157 return context->getExtensions().readFormatBGRA;
158
159 default:
160 return false;
161 }
162}

164bool ValidReadPixelsUnsignedNormalizedDepthType(const Context *context,
165 const gl::InternalFormat *info,
166 GLenum type)
167{
168 bool supportsReadDepthNV = (context->getExtensions().readDepthNV && (info->depthBits > 0) &&
169 (info->componentCount == 1));
170 switch (type)
171 {
172 case GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT:
173 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT:
174 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_24_8:
175 return supportsReadDepthNV;
176 default:
177 return false;
178 }
179}
180
181bool ValidReadPixelsFloatDepthType(const Context *context,
182 const gl::InternalFormat *info,
183 GLenum type)
184{
185 return context->getExtensions().readDepthNV && (type == GL_FLOAT) &&
186 context->getExtensions().depthBufferFloat2NV && (info->componentCount == 1);
187}
188
189bool ValidReadPixelsFormatType(const Context *context,
190 const gl::InternalFormat *info,
191 GLenum format,
192 GLenum type)
193{
194 switch (info->componentType)
195 {
196 case GL_UNSIGNED_NORMALIZED:
197 // TODO(geofflang): Don't accept BGRA here. Some chrome internals appear to try to use
198 // ReadPixels with BGRA even if the extension is not present
199 switch (format)
200 {
201 case GL_RGBA:
202 return ((type == GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE) && info->pixelBytes >= 1) ||
203 (context->getExtensions().textureNorm16 && (type == GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT) &&
204 info->pixelBytes >= 2);
205 case GL_BGRA_EXT:
206 return context->getExtensions().readFormatBGRA && (type == GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE);
207 case GL_STENCIL_INDEX_OES:
208 return context->getExtensions().readStencilNV && (type == GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE);
209 case GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT:
210 return ValidReadPixelsUnsignedNormalizedDepthType(context, info, type);
211 default:
212 return false;
213 }
214 case GL_SIGNED_NORMALIZED:
215 return (format == GL_RGBA && type == GL_BYTE && info->pixelBytes >= 1) ||
216 (context->getExtensions().textureNorm16 && format == GL_RGBA &&
217 type == GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT && info->pixelBytes >= 2);
218
219 case GL_INT:
220 return (format == GL_RGBA_INTEGER && type == GL_INT);
221
222 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT:
223 return (format == GL_RGBA_INTEGER && type == GL_UNSIGNED_INT);
224
225 case GL_FLOAT:
226 switch (format)
227 {
228 case GL_RGBA:
229 return (type == GL_FLOAT);
230 case GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT:
231 return ValidReadPixelsFloatDepthType(context, info, type);
232 default:
233 return false;
234 }
235 default:
236 UNREACHABLE();
237 return false;
238 }
239}

241template <typename ParamType>
242bool ValidateTextureWrapModeValue(const Context *context,
243 const ParamType *params,
244 bool restrictedWrapModes)
245{
246 switch (ConvertToGLenum(params[0]))
247 {
248 case GL_CLAMP_TO_EDGE:
249 break;
250
251 case GL_CLAMP_TO_BORDER:
252 if (!context->getExtensions().textureBorderClampOES)
253 {
254 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kExtensionNotEnabled);
255 return false;
256 }
257 break;
258
259 case GL_REPEAT:
260 case GL_MIRRORED_REPEAT:
261 if (restrictedWrapModes)
262 {
263 // OES_EGL_image_external and ANGLE_texture_rectangle specifies this error.
264 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidWrapModeTexture);
265 return false;
266 }
267 break;
268
269 default:
270 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidTextureWrap);
271 return false;
272 }
273
274 return true;
275}

277template <typename ParamType>
278bool ValidateTextureMinFilterValue(const Context *context,
279 const ParamType *params,
280 bool restrictedMinFilter)
281{
282 switch (ConvertToGLenum(params[0]))
283 {
284 case GL_NEAREST:
285 case GL_LINEAR:
286 break;
287
288 case GL_NEAREST_MIPMAP_NEAREST:
289 case GL_LINEAR_MIPMAP_NEAREST:
290 case GL_NEAREST_MIPMAP_LINEAR:
291 case GL_LINEAR_MIPMAP_LINEAR:
292 if (restrictedMinFilter)
293 {
294 // OES_EGL_image_external specifies this error.
295 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidFilterTexture);
296 return false;
297 }
298 break;
299
300 default:
301 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidTextureFilterParam);
302 return false;
303 }
304
305 return true;
306}

325template <typename ParamType>
326bool ValidateTextureCompareModeValue(const Context *context, const ParamType *params)
327{
328 // Acceptable mode parameters from GLES 3.0.2 spec, table 3.17
329 switch (ConvertToGLenum(params[0]))
330 {
331 case GL_NONE:
332 case GL_COMPARE_REF_TO_TEXTURE:
333 break;
334
335 default:
336 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kUnknownParameter);
337 return false;
338 }
339
340 return true;
341}

345{
346 // Acceptable function parameters from GLES 3.0.2 spec, table 3.17
347 switch (ConvertToGLenum(params[0]))
348 {
349 case GL_LEQUAL:
350 case GL_GEQUAL:
351 case GL_LESS:
352 case GL_GREATER:
353 case GL_EQUAL:
354 case GL_NOTEQUAL:
355 case GL_ALWAYS:
356 case GL_NEVER:
357 break;
358
359 default:
360 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kUnknownParameter);
361 return false;
362 }

364 return true;

413bool ValidateTextureMaxAnisotropyExtensionEnabled(const Context *context)
414{
415 if (!context->getExtensions().textureFilterAnisotropic)
416 {
417 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kExtensionNotEnabled);
418 return false;

423
424bool ValidateTextureMaxAnisotropyValue(const Context *context, GLfloat paramValue)
425{
426 if (!ValidateTextureMaxAnisotropyExtensionEnabled(context))
427 {
428 return false;
429 }
430
431 GLfloat largest = context->getExtensions().maxTextureAnisotropy;
432
433 if (paramValue < 1 || paramValue > largest)
434 {
435 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kOutsideOfBounds);
436 return false;
437 }
438
439 return true;
440}

442bool ValidateFragmentShaderColorBufferMaskMatch(const Context *context)
443{
444 const Program *program = context->getActiveLinkedProgram();
445 const Framebuffer *framebuffer = context->getState().getDrawFramebuffer();
446
447 auto drawBufferMask = framebuffer->getDrawBufferMask().to_ulong();
448 auto fragmentOutputMask = program->getActiveOutputVariables().to_ulong();
449
450 return drawBufferMask == (drawBufferMask & fragmentOutputMask);
451}
452
453bool ValidateFragmentShaderColorBufferTypeMatch(const Context *context)
454{
455 const Program *program = context->getActiveLinkedProgram();
456 const Framebuffer *framebuffer = context->getState().getDrawFramebuffer();
457
458 return ValidateComponentTypeMasks(program->getDrawBufferTypeMask().to_ulong(),
459 framebuffer->getDrawBufferTypeMask().to_ulong(),
460 program->getActiveOutputVariables().to_ulong(),
461 framebuffer->getDrawBufferMask().to_ulong());
462}
463
464bool ValidateVertexShaderAttributeTypeMatch(const Context *context)
465{
466 const auto &glState = context->getState();
467 const Program *program = context->getActiveLinkedProgram();
468 const VertexArray *vao = context->getState().getVertexArray();
469
470 if (!program)
471 {
472 return false;
473 }
474
475 unsigned long stateCurrentValuesTypeBits = glState.getCurrentValuesTypeMask().to_ulong();
476 unsigned long vaoAttribTypeBits = vao->getAttributesTypeMask().to_ulong();
477 unsigned long vaoAttribEnabledMask = vao->getAttributesMask().to_ulong();
478
479 vaoAttribEnabledMask |= vaoAttribEnabledMask << kMaxComponentTypeMaskIndex;
480 vaoAttribTypeBits = (vaoAttribEnabledMask & vaoAttribTypeBits);
481 vaoAttribTypeBits |= (~vaoAttribEnabledMask & stateCurrentValuesTypeBits);
482
483 const ProgramExecutable &executable = program->getExecutable();
484 return ValidateComponentTypeMasks(executable.getAttributesTypeMask().to_ulong(),
485 vaoAttribTypeBits, executable.getAttributesMask().to_ulong(),
486 0xFFFF);
487}

489bool IsCompatibleDrawModeWithGeometryShader(PrimitiveMode drawMode,
490 PrimitiveMode geometryShaderInputPrimitiveType)
491{
492 // [EXT_geometry_shader] Section 11.1gs.1, Geometry Shader Input Primitives
493 switch (drawMode)
494 {
495 case PrimitiveMode::Points:
496 return geometryShaderInputPrimitiveType == PrimitiveMode::Points;
497 case PrimitiveMode::Lines:
498 case PrimitiveMode::LineStrip:
499 case PrimitiveMode::LineLoop:
500 return geometryShaderInputPrimitiveType == PrimitiveMode::Lines;
501 case PrimitiveMode::LinesAdjacency:
502 case PrimitiveMode::LineStripAdjacency:
503 return geometryShaderInputPrimitiveType == PrimitiveMode::LinesAdjacency;
504 case PrimitiveMode::Triangles:
505 case PrimitiveMode::TriangleFan:
506 case PrimitiveMode::TriangleStrip:
507 return geometryShaderInputPrimitiveType == PrimitiveMode::Triangles;
508 case PrimitiveMode::TrianglesAdjacency:
509 case PrimitiveMode::TriangleStripAdjacency:
510 return geometryShaderInputPrimitiveType == PrimitiveMode::TrianglesAdjacency;
511 default:
512 UNREACHABLE();
513 return false;
514 }
515}

523 case GL_TEXTURE_MIN_FILTER:
524 case GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_S:
525 case GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_T:
526 case GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_R:
527 case GL_GENERATE_MIPMAP:

531 return false;
532 }

540ANGLE_INLINE const char *ValidateProgramDrawStates(const State &state,
541 const Extensions &extensions,
542 Program *program)
543{
544 if (extensions.multiview || extensions.multiview2)
545 {
546 const int programNumViews = program->usesMultiview() ? program->getNumViews() : 1;
547 Framebuffer *framebuffer = state.getDrawFramebuffer();
548 const int framebufferNumViews = framebuffer->getNumViews();
549
550 if (framebufferNumViews != programNumViews)
551 {
552 return gl::err::kMultiviewMismatch;
553 }
554
555 if (state.isTransformFeedbackActiveUnpaused() && framebufferNumViews > 1)
556 {
557 return gl::err::kMultiviewTransformFeedback;
558 }
559
560 if (extensions.disjointTimerQuery && framebufferNumViews > 1 &&
561 state.isQueryActive(QueryType::TimeElapsed))
562 {
563 return gl::err::kMultiviewTimerQuery;
564 }
565 }
566
567 // Uniform buffer validation
568 for (unsigned int uniformBlockIndex = 0;
569 uniformBlockIndex < program->getActiveUniformBlockCount(); uniformBlockIndex++)
570 {
571 const InterfaceBlock &uniformBlock = program->getUniformBlockByIndex(uniformBlockIndex);
572 GLuint blockBinding = program->getUniformBlockBinding(uniformBlockIndex);
573 const OffsetBindingPointer<Buffer> &uniformBuffer =
574 state.getIndexedUniformBuffer(blockBinding);
575
576 if (uniformBuffer.get() == nullptr)
577 {
578 // undefined behaviour
579 return gl::err::kUniformBufferUnbound;
580 }
581
582 size_t uniformBufferSize = GetBoundBufferAvailableSize(uniformBuffer);
583 if (uniformBufferSize < uniformBlock.dataSize)
584 {
585 // undefined behaviour
586 return gl::err::kUniformBufferTooSmall;
587 }
588
589 if (extensions.webglCompatibility &&
590 uniformBuffer->isBoundForTransformFeedbackAndOtherUse())
591 {
592 return gl::err::kUniformBufferBoundForTransformFeedback;
593 }
594 }
595
596 return nullptr;
597}

600void SetRobustLengthParam(const GLsizei *length, GLsizei value)
601{
602 if (length)
603 {
604 // Currently we modify robust length parameters in the validation layer. We should be only
605 // doing this in the Context instead.
606 // TODO(http://anglebug.com/4406): Remove when possible.
607 *const_cast<GLsizei *>(length) = value;
608 }

611bool ValidTextureTarget(const Context *context, TextureType type)
612{
613 switch (type)
614 {
615 case TextureType::_2D:
616 case TextureType::CubeMap:
617 return true;
618
619 case TextureType::Rectangle:
620 return context->getExtensions().textureRectangle;
621
622 case TextureType::_3D:
623 return ((context->getClientMajorVersion() >= 3) ||
624 context->getExtensions().texture3DOES);
625
626 case TextureType::_2DArray:
627 return (context->getClientMajorVersion() >= 3);
628
629 case TextureType::_2DMultisample:
630 return (context->getClientVersion() >= Version(3, 1) ||
631 context->getExtensions().textureMultisample);
632 case TextureType::_2DMultisampleArray:
633 return context->getExtensions().textureStorageMultisample2DArrayOES;
634
635 case TextureType::CubeMapArray:
636 return (context->getClientVersion() >= Version(3, 2) ||
637 context->getExtensions().textureCubeMapArrayAny());
638
639 case TextureType::VideoImage:
640 return context->getExtensions().webglVideoTexture;
641
642 case TextureType::Buffer:
643 return (context->getClientVersion() >= Version(3, 2) ||
644 context->getExtensions().textureBufferAny());
645
646 default:
647 return false;
648 }
649}
650
651bool ValidTexture2DTarget(const Context *context, TextureType type)
652{
653 switch (type)
654 {
655 case TextureType::_2D:
656 case TextureType::CubeMap:
657 return true;
658
659 case TextureType::Rectangle:
660 return context->getExtensions().textureRectangle;
661
662 default:
663 return false;
664 }
665}
666
667bool ValidTexture3DTarget(const Context *context, TextureType target)
668{
669 switch (target)
670 {
671 case TextureType::_3D:
672 case TextureType::_2DArray:
673 return (context->getClientMajorVersion() >= 3);
674
675 case TextureType::CubeMapArray:
676 return (context->getClientVersion() >= Version(3, 2) ||
677 context->getExtensions().textureCubeMapArrayAny());
678
679 default:
680 return false;
681 }
682}

684// Most texture GL calls are not compatible with external textures, so we have a separate validation
685// function for use in the GL calls that do
686bool ValidTextureExternalTarget(const Context *context, TextureType target)
687{
688 return (target == TextureType::External) &&
689 (context->getExtensions().eglImageExternalOES ||
690 context->getExtensions().eglStreamConsumerExternalNV);
691}
692
693bool ValidTextureExternalTarget(const Context *context, TextureTarget target)
694{
695 return (target == TextureTarget::External) &&
696 ValidTextureExternalTarget(context, TextureType::External);
697}
698
699// This function differs from ValidTextureTarget in that the target must be
700// usable as the destination of a 2D operation-- so a cube face is valid, but
701// GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP is not.
702// Note: duplicate of IsInternalTextureTarget
703bool ValidTexture2DDestinationTarget(const Context *context, TextureTarget target)
704{
705 switch (target)
706 {
707 case TextureTarget::_2D:
708 case TextureTarget::CubeMapNegativeX:
709 case TextureTarget::CubeMapNegativeY:
710 case TextureTarget::CubeMapNegativeZ:
711 case TextureTarget::CubeMapPositiveX:
712 case TextureTarget::CubeMapPositiveY:
713 case TextureTarget::CubeMapPositiveZ:
714 return true;
715 case TextureTarget::Rectangle:
716 return context->getExtensions().textureRectangle;
717 case TextureTarget::VideoImage:
718 return context->getExtensions().webglVideoTexture;
719 default:
720 return false;
721 }
722}

724bool ValidateTransformFeedbackPrimitiveMode(const Context *context,
725 PrimitiveMode transformFeedbackPrimitiveMode,
726 PrimitiveMode renderPrimitiveMode)
727{
728 ASSERT(context);
729
730 if (!context->getExtensions().geometryShader)
731 {
732 // It is an invalid operation to call DrawArrays or DrawArraysInstanced with a draw mode
733 // that does not match the current transform feedback object's draw mode (if transform
734 // feedback is active), (3.0.2, section 2.14, pg 86)
735 return transformFeedbackPrimitiveMode == renderPrimitiveMode;
736 }
737
738 // [GL_EXT_geometry_shader] Table 12.1gs
739 switch (renderPrimitiveMode)
740 {
741 case PrimitiveMode::Points:
742 return transformFeedbackPrimitiveMode == PrimitiveMode::Points;
743 case PrimitiveMode::Lines:
744 case PrimitiveMode::LineStrip:
745 case PrimitiveMode::LineLoop:
746 return transformFeedbackPrimitiveMode == PrimitiveMode::Lines;
747 case PrimitiveMode::Triangles:
748 case PrimitiveMode::TriangleFan:
749 case PrimitiveMode::TriangleStrip:
750 return transformFeedbackPrimitiveMode == PrimitiveMode::Triangles;
751 default:
752 UNREACHABLE();
753 return false;
754 }
755}

757bool ValidateDrawElementsInstancedBase(const Context *context,
758 PrimitiveMode mode,
759 GLsizei count,
760 DrawElementsType type,
761 const void *indices,
762 GLsizei primcount)
763{
764 if (primcount <= 0)
765 {
766 if (primcount < 0)
767 {
768 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kNegativePrimcount);
769 return false;
770 }
771
772 // Early exit.
773 return ValidateDrawElementsCommon(context, mode, count, type, indices, primcount);
774 }

776 if (!ValidateDrawElementsCommon(context, mode, count, type, indices, primcount))
777 {
778 return false;
779 }
780
781 if (count == 0)
782 {
783 // Early exit.
784 return true;
785 }
786
787 return ValidateDrawInstancedAttribs(context, primcount);
788}
789
790bool ValidateDrawArraysInstancedBase(const Context *context,
791 PrimitiveMode mode,
792 GLint first,
793 GLsizei count,
794 GLsizei primcount)
795{
796 if (primcount <= 0)
797 {
798 if (primcount < 0)
799 {
800 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kNegativePrimcount);
801 return false;
802 }
803
804 // Early exit.
805 return ValidateDrawArraysCommon(context, mode, first, count, primcount);
806 }
807
808 if (!ValidateDrawArraysCommon(context, mode, first, count, primcount))
809 {
810 return false;
811 }
812
813 if (count == 0)
814 {
815 // Early exit.
816 return true;
817 }
818
819 return ValidateDrawInstancedAttribs(context, primcount);
820}

822bool ValidateDrawInstancedANGLE(const Context *context)
823{
824 // Verify there is at least one active attribute with a divisor of zero
825 const State &state = context->getState();
826 const ProgramExecutable *executable = state.getProgramExecutable();
827
828 if (!executable)
829 {
830 // No executable means there is no Program/PPO bound, which is undefined behavior, but isn't
831 // an error.
832 context->getState().getDebug().insertMessage(
833 GL_DEBUG_SOURCE_API, GL_DEBUG_TYPE_UNDEFINED_BEHAVIOR, 0, GL_DEBUG_SEVERITY_HIGH,
834 std::string("Attempting to draw without a program"), gl::LOG_WARN);
835 return true;
836 }
837
838 const auto &attribs = state.getVertexArray()->getVertexAttributes();
839 const auto &bindings = state.getVertexArray()->getVertexBindings();
840 for (size_t attributeIndex = 0; attributeIndex < MAX_VERTEX_ATTRIBS; attributeIndex++)
841 {
842 const VertexAttribute &attrib = attribs[attributeIndex];
843 const VertexBinding &binding = bindings[attrib.bindingIndex];
844 if (executable->isAttribLocationActive(attributeIndex) && binding.getDivisor() == 0)
845 {
846 return true;
847 }
848 }
849
850 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kNoZeroDivisor);
851 return false;
852}

913bool ValidMipLevel(const Context *context, TextureType type, GLint level)
914{
915 const auto &caps = context->getCaps();
916 int maxDimension = 0;
917 switch (type)
918 {
919 case TextureType::_2D:
920 case TextureType::_2DArray:
921 case TextureType::_2DMultisample:
922 case TextureType::_2DMultisampleArray:
923 // TODO(http://anglebug.com/2775): It's a bit unclear what the "maximum allowable
924 // level-of-detail" for multisample textures should be. Could maybe make it zero.
925 maxDimension = caps.max2DTextureSize;
926 break;
927
928 case TextureType::CubeMap:
929 case TextureType::CubeMapArray:
930 maxDimension = caps.maxCubeMapTextureSize;
931 break;
932
933 case TextureType::External:
934 case TextureType::Rectangle:
935 case TextureType::VideoImage:
936 case TextureType::Buffer:
937 return level == 0;
938
939 case TextureType::_3D:
940 maxDimension = caps.max3DTextureSize;
941 break;
942
943 default:
944 UNREACHABLE();
945 }
946
947 return level <= log2(maxDimension) && level >= 0;
948}

950bool ValidImageSizeParameters(const Context *context,
951 TextureType target,
952 GLint level,
953 GLsizei width,
954 GLsizei height,
955 GLsizei depth,
956 bool isSubImage)
957{
958 if (width < 0 || height < 0 || depth < 0)
959 {
960 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kNegativeSize);
961 return false;
962 }
963 // TexSubImage parameters can be NPOT without textureNPOT extension,
964 // as long as the destination texture is POT.
965 bool hasNPOTSupport =
966 context->getExtensions().textureNPOTOES || context->getClientVersion() >= Version(3, 0);
967 if (!isSubImage && !hasNPOTSupport &&
968 (level != 0 && (!isPow2(width) || !isPow2(height) || !isPow2(depth))))
969 {
970 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kTextureNotPow2);
971 return false;
972 }
973
974 if (!ValidMipLevel(context, target, level))
975 {
976 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidMipLevel);
977 return false;
978 }
979
980 return true;
981}

988bool ValidCompressedImageSize(const Context *context,
989 GLenum internalFormat,
990 GLint level,
991 GLsizei width,
992 GLsizei height,
993 GLsizei depth)
994{
995 const InternalFormat &formatInfo = GetSizedInternalFormatInfo(internalFormat);
996 if (!formatInfo.compressed)
997 {
998 return false;
999 }
1000
1001 if (width < 0 || height < 0)
1002 {
1003 return false;
1004 }
1005
1006 if (CompressedTextureFormatRequiresExactSize(internalFormat))
1007 {
1008 if (!ValidCompressedDimension(width, formatInfo.compressedBlockWidth, level) ||
1009 !ValidCompressedDimension(height, formatInfo.compressedBlockHeight, level) ||
1010 !ValidCompressedDimension(depth, formatInfo.compressedBlockDepth, level))
1011 {
1012 return false;
1013 }
1014 }
1015
1016 return true;
1017}
1018
1019bool ValidCompressedSubImageSize(const Context *context,
1020 GLenum internalFormat,
1021 GLint xoffset,
1022 GLint yoffset,
1023 GLint zoffset,
1024 GLsizei width,
1025 GLsizei height,
1026 GLsizei depth,
1027 size_t textureWidth,
1028 size_t textureHeight,
1029 size_t textureDepth)
1030{
1031 const InternalFormat &formatInfo = GetSizedInternalFormatInfo(internalFormat);
1032 if (!formatInfo.compressed)
1033 {
1034 return false;
1035 }
1036
1037 if (xoffset < 0 || yoffset < 0 || zoffset < 0 || width < 0 || height < 0 || depth < 0)
1038 {
1039 return false;
1040 }
1041
1042 bool fillsEntireMip =
1043 xoffset == 0 && yoffset == 0 && static_cast<size_t>(width) == textureWidth &&
1044 static_cast<size_t>(height) == textureHeight && static_cast<size_t>(depth) == textureDepth;
1045
1046 if (CompressedFormatRequiresWholeImage(internalFormat))
1047 {
1048 return fillsEntireMip;
1049 }
1050
1051 if (CompressedSubTextureFormatRequiresExactSize(internalFormat))
1052 {
1053 if (xoffset % formatInfo.compressedBlockWidth != 0 ||
1054 yoffset % formatInfo.compressedBlockHeight != 0 ||
1055 zoffset % formatInfo.compressedBlockDepth != 0)
1056 {
1057 return false;
1058 }
1059
1060 // Allowed to either have data that is a multiple of block size or is smaller than the block
1061 // size but fills the entire mip
1062 bool sizeMultipleOfBlockSize = (width % formatInfo.compressedBlockWidth) == 0 &&
1063 (height % formatInfo.compressedBlockHeight) == 0 &&
1064 (depth % formatInfo.compressedBlockDepth) == 0;
1065 if (!sizeMultipleOfBlockSize && !fillsEntireMip)
1066 {
1067 return false;
1068 }
1069 }
1070
1071 return true;
1072}
1073
1074bool ValidImageDataSize(const Context *context,
1075 TextureType texType,
1076 GLsizei width,
1077 GLsizei height,
1078 GLsizei depth,
1079 GLenum format,
1080 GLenum type,
1081 const void *pixels,
1082 GLsizei imageSize)
1083{
1084 Buffer *pixelUnpackBuffer = context->getState().getTargetBuffer(BufferBinding::PixelUnpack);
1085 if (pixelUnpackBuffer == nullptr && imageSize < 0)
1086 {
1087 // Checks are not required
1088 return true;
1089 }
1090
1091 // ...the data would be unpacked from the buffer object such that the memory reads required
1092 // would exceed the data store size.
1093 const InternalFormat &formatInfo = GetInternalFormatInfo(format, type);
1094 ASSERT(formatInfo.internalFormat != GL_NONE);
1095 const Extents size(width, height, depth);
1096 const auto &unpack = context->getState().getUnpackState();
1097
1098 bool targetIs3D = texType == TextureType::_3D || texType == TextureType::_2DArray;
1099 GLuint endByte = 0;
1100 if (!formatInfo.computePackUnpackEndByte(type, size, unpack, targetIs3D, &endByte))
1101 {
1102 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kIntegerOverflow);
1103 return false;
1104 }
1105
1106 if (pixelUnpackBuffer)
1107 {
1108 CheckedNumeric<size_t> checkedEndByte(endByte);
1109 CheckedNumeric<size_t> checkedOffset(reinterpret_cast<size_t>(pixels));
1110 checkedEndByte += checkedOffset;
1111
1112 if (!checkedEndByte.IsValid() ||
1113 (checkedEndByte.ValueOrDie() > static_cast<size_t>(pixelUnpackBuffer->getSize())))
1114 {
1115 // Overflow past the end of the buffer
1116 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kIntegerOverflow);
1117 return false;
1118 }
1119 if (context->getExtensions().webglCompatibility &&
1120 pixelUnpackBuffer->isBoundForTransformFeedbackAndOtherUse())
1121 {
1122 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION,
1123 kPixelUnpackBufferBoundForTransformFeedback);
1124 return false;
1125 }
1126 }
1127 else
1128 {
1129 ASSERT(imageSize >= 0);
1130 if (pixels == nullptr && imageSize != 0)
1131 {
1132 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kImageSizeMustBeZero);
1133 return false;
1134 }
1135
1136 if (pixels != nullptr && endByte > static_cast<GLuint>(imageSize))
1137 {
1138 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kImageSizeTooSmall);
1139 return false;
1140 }
1141 }
1142
1143 return true;
1144}

1166
1167bool ValidateWebGLVertexAttribPointer(const Context *context,
1168 VertexAttribType type,
1169 GLboolean normalized,
1170 GLsizei stride,
1171 const void *ptr,
1172 bool pureInteger)
1173{
1174 ASSERT(context->getExtensions().webglCompatibility);
1175 // WebGL 1.0 [Section 6.11] Vertex Attribute Data Stride
1176 // The WebGL API supports vertex attribute data strides up to 255 bytes. A call to
1177 // vertexAttribPointer will generate an INVALID_VALUE error if the value for the stride
1178 // parameter exceeds 255.
1179 constexpr GLsizei kMaxWebGLStride = 255;
1180 if (stride > kMaxWebGLStride)
1181 {
1182 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kStrideExceedsWebGLLimit);
1183 return false;
1184 }
1185
1186 // WebGL 1.0 [Section 6.4] Buffer Offset and Stride Requirements
1187 // The offset arguments to drawElements and vertexAttribPointer, and the stride argument to
1188 // vertexAttribPointer, must be a multiple of the size of the data type passed to the call,
1189 // or an INVALID_OPERATION error is generated.
1190 angle::FormatID internalType = GetVertexFormatID(type, normalized, 1, pureInteger);
1191 size_t typeSize = GetVertexFormatSize(internalType);
1192
1193 ASSERT(isPow2(typeSize) && typeSize > 0);
1194 size_t sizeMask = (typeSize - 1);
1195 if ((reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(ptr) & sizeMask) != 0)
1196 {
1197 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kOffsetMustBeMultipleOfType);
1198 return false;
1199 }
1200
1201 if ((stride & sizeMask) != 0)
1202 {
1203 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kStrideMustBeMultipleOfType);
1204 return false;
1205 }
1206
1207 return true;
1208}
1209
1210Program *GetValidProgramNoResolve(const Context *context, ShaderProgramID id)
1211{
1212 // ES3 spec (section 2.11.1) -- "Commands that accept shader or program object names will
1213 // generate the error INVALID_VALUE if the provided name is not the name of either a shader
1214 // or program object and INVALID_OPERATION if the provided name identifies an object
1215 // that is not the expected type."
1216
1217 Program *validProgram = context->getProgramNoResolveLink(id);
1218
1219 if (!validProgram)
1220 {
1221 if (context->getShader(id))
1222 {
1223 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kExpectedProgramName);
1224 }
1225 else
1226 {
1227 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidProgramName);
1228 }
1229 }
1230
1231 return validProgram;
1232}
1233
1234Program *GetValidProgram(const Context *context, ShaderProgramID id)
1235{
1236 Program *program = GetValidProgramNoResolve(context, id);
1237 if (program)
1238 {
1239 program->resolveLink(context);
1240 }
1241 return program;
1242}
1243
1244Shader *GetValidShader(const Context *context, ShaderProgramID id)
1245{
1246 // See ValidProgram for spec details.
1247
1248 Shader *validShader = context->getShader(id);
1249
1250 if (!validShader)
1251 {
1252 if (context->getProgramNoResolveLink(id))
1253 {
1254 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kExpectedShaderName);
1255 }
1256 else
1257 {
1258 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidShaderName);
1259 }
1260 }
1261
1262 return validShader;
1263}

1265bool ValidateAttachmentTarget(const Context *context, GLenum attachment)
1266{
1267 if (attachment >= GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT1_EXT && attachment <= GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT15_EXT)
1268 {
1269 if (context->getClientMajorVersion() < 3 && !context->getExtensions().drawBuffers)
1270 {
1271 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidAttachment);
1272 return false;
1273 }
1274
1275 // Color attachment 0 is validated below because it is always valid
1276 const int colorAttachment = (attachment - GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0_EXT);
1277 if (colorAttachment >= context->getCaps().maxColorAttachments)
1278 {
1279 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidAttachment);
1280 return false;
1281 }
1282 }
1283 else
1284 {
1285 switch (attachment)
1286 {
1287 case GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0:
1288 case GL_DEPTH_ATTACHMENT:
1289 case GL_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT:
1290 break;
1291
1292 case GL_DEPTH_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT:
1293 if (!context->getExtensions().webglCompatibility &&
1294 context->getClientMajorVersion() < 3)
1295 {
1296 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidAttachment);
1297 return false;
1298 }
1299 break;
1300
1301 default:
1302 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidAttachment);
1303 return false;
1304 }
1305 }
1306
1307 return true;
1308}

1310bool ValidateRenderbufferStorageParametersBase(const Context *context,
1311 GLenum target,
1312 GLsizei samples,
1313 GLenum internalformat,
1314 GLsizei width,
1315 GLsizei height)
1316{
1317 switch (target)
1318 {
1319 case GL_RENDERBUFFER:
1320 break;
1321 default:
1322 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidRenderbufferTarget);
1323 return false;
1324 }
1325
1326 if (width < 0 || height < 0 || samples < 0)
1327 {
1328 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidRenderbufferWidthHeight);
1329 return false;
1330 }
1331
1332 // Hack for the special WebGL 1 "DEPTH_STENCIL" internal format.
1333 GLenum convertedInternalFormat = context->getConvertedRenderbufferFormat(internalformat);
1334
1335 const TextureCaps &formatCaps = context->getTextureCaps().get(convertedInternalFormat);
1336 if (!formatCaps.renderbuffer)
1337 {
1338 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidRenderbufferInternalFormat);
1339 return false;
1340 }
1341
1342 // ANGLE_framebuffer_multisample does not explicitly state that the internal format must be
1343 // sized but it does state that the format must be in the ES2.0 spec table 4.5 which contains
1344 // only sized internal formats.
1345 const InternalFormat &formatInfo = GetSizedInternalFormatInfo(convertedInternalFormat);
1346 if (formatInfo.internalFormat == GL_NONE)
1347 {
1348 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidRenderbufferInternalFormat);
1349 return false;
1350 }
1351
1352 if (std::max(width, height) > context->getCaps().maxRenderbufferSize)
1353 {
1354 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kResourceMaxRenderbufferSize);
1355 return false;
1356 }
1357
1358 RenderbufferID id = context->getState().getRenderbufferId();
1359 if (id.value == 0)
1360 {
1361 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidRenderbufferTarget);
1362 return false;
1363 }
1364
1365 return true;
1366}
1367
1368bool ValidateFramebufferRenderbufferParameters(const Context *context,
1369 GLenum target,
1370 GLenum attachment,
1371 GLenum renderbuffertarget,
1372 RenderbufferID renderbuffer)
1373{
1374 if (!ValidFramebufferTarget(context, target))
1375 {
1376 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidFramebufferTarget);
1377 return false;
1378 }
1379
1380 Framebuffer *framebuffer = context->getState().getTargetFramebuffer(target);
1381
1382 ASSERT(framebuffer);
1383 if (framebuffer->isDefault())
1384 {
1385 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kDefaultFramebufferTarget);
1386 return false;
1387 }
1388
1389 if (!ValidateAttachmentTarget(context, attachment))
1390 {
1391 return false;
1392 }
1393
1394 // [OpenGL ES 2.0.25] Section 4.4.3 page 112
1395 // [OpenGL ES 3.0.2] Section 4.4.2 page 201
1396 // 'renderbuffer' must be either zero or the name of an existing renderbuffer object of
1397 // type 'renderbuffertarget', otherwise an INVALID_OPERATION error is generated.
1398 if (renderbuffer.value != 0)
1399 {
1400 if (!context->getRenderbuffer(renderbuffer))
1401 {
1402 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidRenderbufferTarget);
1403 return false;
1404 }
1405 }
1406
1407 return true;
1408}
1409
1410bool ValidateBlitFramebufferParameters(const Context *context,
1411 GLint srcX0,
1412 GLint srcY0,
1413 GLint srcX1,
1414 GLint srcY1,
1415 GLint dstX0,
1416 GLint dstY0,
1417 GLint dstX1,
1418 GLint dstY1,
1419 GLbitfield mask,
1420 GLenum filter)
1421{
1422 switch (filter)
1423 {
1424 case GL_NEAREST:
1425 break;
1426 case GL_LINEAR:
1427 break;
1428 default:
1429 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kBlitInvalidFilter);
1430 return false;
1431 }
1432
1433 if ((mask & ~(GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT | GL_STENCIL_BUFFER_BIT | GL_DEPTH_BUFFER_BIT)) != 0)
1434 {
1435 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kBlitInvalidMask);
1436 return false;
1437 }
1438
1439 // ES3.0 spec, section 4.3.2 states that linear filtering is only available for the
1440 // color buffer, leaving only nearest being unfiltered from above
1441 if ((mask & ~GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT) != 0 && filter != GL_NEAREST)
1442 {
1443 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBlitOnlyNearestForNonColor);
1444 return false;
1445 }
1446
1447 const auto &glState = context->getState();
1448 Framebuffer *readFramebuffer = glState.getReadFramebuffer();
1449 Framebuffer *drawFramebuffer = glState.getDrawFramebuffer();
1450
1451 if (!readFramebuffer || !drawFramebuffer)
1452 {
1453 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_FRAMEBUFFER_OPERATION, kBlitFramebufferMissing);
1454 return false;
1455 }
1456
1457 if (!ValidateFramebufferComplete(context, readFramebuffer))
1458 {
1459 return false;
1460 }
1461
1462 if (!ValidateFramebufferComplete(context, drawFramebuffer))
1463 {
1464 return false;
1465 }
1466
1467 // The draw and read framebuffers can only match if:
1468 // - They are the default framebuffer AND
1469 // - The read/draw surfaces are different
1470 if ((readFramebuffer->id() == drawFramebuffer->id()) &&
1471 ((drawFramebuffer->id() != Framebuffer::kDefaultDrawFramebufferHandle) ||
1472 (context->getCurrentDrawSurface() == context->getCurrentReadSurface())))
1473 {
1474 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBlitFeedbackLoop);
1475 return false;
1476 }
1477
1478 // Not allow blitting to MS buffers, therefore if renderToTextureSamples exist,
1479 // consider it MS. checkReadBufferResourceSamples = false
1480 if (!ValidateFramebufferNotMultisampled(context, drawFramebuffer, false))
1481 {
1482 return false;
1483 }
1484
1485 // This validation is specified in the WebGL 2.0 spec and not in the GLES 3.0.5 spec, but we
1486 // always run it in order to avoid triggering driver bugs.
1487 if (DifferenceCanOverflow(srcX0, srcX1) || DifferenceCanOverflow(srcY0, srcY1) ||
1488 DifferenceCanOverflow(dstX0, dstX1) || DifferenceCanOverflow(dstY0, dstY1))
1489 {
1490 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kBlitDimensionsOutOfRange);
1491 return false;
1492 }
1493
1494 bool sameBounds = srcX0 == dstX0 && srcY0 == dstY0 && srcX1 == dstX1 && srcY1 == dstY1;
1495
1496 if (mask & GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT)
1497 {
1498 const FramebufferAttachment *readColorBuffer = readFramebuffer->getReadColorAttachment();
1499 const Extensions &extensions = context->getExtensions();
1500
1501 if (readColorBuffer)
1502 {
1503 const Format &readFormat = readColorBuffer->getFormat();
1504
1505 for (size_t drawbufferIdx = 0;
1506 drawbufferIdx < drawFramebuffer->getDrawbufferStateCount(); ++drawbufferIdx)
1507 {
1508 const FramebufferAttachment *attachment =
1509 drawFramebuffer->getDrawBuffer(drawbufferIdx);
1510 if (attachment)
1511 {
1512 const Format &drawFormat = attachment->getFormat();
1513
1514 // The GL ES 3.0.2 spec (pg 193) states that:
1515 // 1) If the read buffer is fixed point format, the draw buffer must be as well
1516 // 2) If the read buffer is an unsigned integer format, the draw buffer must be
1517 // as well
1518 // 3) If the read buffer is a signed integer format, the draw buffer must be as
1519 // well
1520 // Changes with EXT_color_buffer_float:
1521 // Case 1) is changed to fixed point OR floating point
1522 GLenum readComponentType = readFormat.info->componentType;
1523 GLenum drawComponentType = drawFormat.info->componentType;
1524 bool readFixedPoint = (readComponentType == GL_UNSIGNED_NORMALIZED ||
1525 readComponentType == GL_SIGNED_NORMALIZED);
1526 bool drawFixedPoint = (drawComponentType == GL_UNSIGNED_NORMALIZED ||
1527 drawComponentType == GL_SIGNED_NORMALIZED);
1528
1529 if (extensions.colorBufferFloat)
1530 {
1531 bool readFixedOrFloat = (readFixedPoint || readComponentType == GL_FLOAT);
1532 bool drawFixedOrFloat = (drawFixedPoint || drawComponentType == GL_FLOAT);
1533
1534 if (readFixedOrFloat != drawFixedOrFloat)
1535 {
1536 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION,
1537 kBlitTypeMismatchFixedOrFloat);
1538 return false;
1539 }
1540 }
1541 else if (readFixedPoint != drawFixedPoint)
1542 {
1543 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBlitTypeMismatchFixedPoint);
1544 return false;
1545 }
1546
1547 if (readComponentType == GL_UNSIGNED_INT &&
1548 drawComponentType != GL_UNSIGNED_INT)
1549 {
1550 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION,
1551 kBlitTypeMismatchUnsignedInteger);
1552 return false;
1553 }
1554
1555 if (readComponentType == GL_INT && drawComponentType != GL_INT)
1556 {
1557 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION,
1558 kBlitTypeMismatchSignedInteger);
1559 return false;
1560 }
1561
1562 if (readColorBuffer->getResourceSamples() > 0 &&
1563 (!Format::EquivalentForBlit(readFormat, drawFormat) || !sameBounds))
1564 {
1565 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION,
1566 kBlitMultisampledFormatOrBoundsMismatch);
1567 return false;
1568 }
1569
1570 if (context->getExtensions().webglCompatibility &&
1571 *readColorBuffer == *attachment)
1572 {
1573 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBlitSameImageColor);
1574 return false;
1575 }
1576 }
1577 }
1578
1579 if (readFormat.info->isInt() && filter == GL_LINEAR)
1580 {
1581 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBlitIntegerWithLinearFilter);
1582 return false;
1583 }
1584 }
1585 // WebGL 2.0 BlitFramebuffer when blitting from a missing attachment
1586 // In OpenGL ES it is undefined what happens when an operation tries to blit from a missing
1587 // attachment and WebGL defines it to be an error. We do the check unconditionally as the
1588 // situation is an application error that would lead to a crash in ANGLE.
1589 else if (drawFramebuffer->hasEnabledDrawBuffer())
1590 {
1591 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBlitMissingColor);
1592 return false;
1593 }
1594 }
1595
1596 GLenum masks[] = {GL_DEPTH_BUFFER_BIT, GL_STENCIL_BUFFER_BIT};
1597 GLenum attachments[] = {GL_DEPTH_ATTACHMENT, GL_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT};
1598 for (size_t i = 0; i < 2; i++)
1599 {
1600 if (mask & masks[i])
1601 {
1602 const FramebufferAttachment *readBuffer =
1603 readFramebuffer->getAttachment(context, attachments[i]);
1604 const FramebufferAttachment *drawBuffer =
1605 drawFramebuffer->getAttachment(context, attachments[i]);
1606
1607 if (readBuffer && drawBuffer)
1608 {
1609 if (!Format::EquivalentForBlit(readBuffer->getFormat(), drawBuffer->getFormat()))
1610 {
1611 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION,
1612 kBlitDepthOrStencilFormatMismatch);
1613 return false;
1614 }
1615
1616 if (readBuffer->getResourceSamples() > 0 && !sameBounds)
1617 {
1618 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBlitMultisampledBoundsMismatch);
1619 return false;
1620 }
1621
1622 if (context->getExtensions().webglCompatibility && *readBuffer == *drawBuffer)
1623 {
1624 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBlitSameImageDepthOrStencil);
1625 return false;
1626 }
1627 }
1628 // WebGL 2.0 BlitFramebuffer when blitting from a missing attachment
1629 else if (drawBuffer)
1630 {
1631 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBlitMissingDepthOrStencil);
1632 return false;
1633 }
1634 }
1635 }
1636
1637 // OVR_multiview2:
1638 // Calling BlitFramebuffer will result in an INVALID_FRAMEBUFFER_OPERATION error if the
1639 // current draw framebuffer isMultiview() or the number of
1640 // views in the current read framebuffer is more than one.
1641 if (readFramebuffer->readDisallowedByMultiview())
1642 {
1643 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_FRAMEBUFFER_OPERATION, kBlitFromMultiview);
1644 return false;
1645 }
1646 if (drawFramebuffer->isMultiview())
1647 {
1648 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_FRAMEBUFFER_OPERATION, kBlitToMultiview);
1649 return false;
1650 }
1651
1652 return true;
1653}

1790
1791bool ValidateBeginQueryBase(const Context *context, QueryType target, QueryID id)
1792{
1793 if (!ValidQueryType(context, target))
1794 {
1795 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidQueryType);
1796 return false;
1797 }
1798
1799 if (id.value == 0)
1800 {
1801 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidQueryId);
1802 return false;
1803 }
1804
1805 // From EXT_occlusion_query_boolean: If BeginQueryEXT is called with an <id>
1806 // of zero, if the active query object name for <target> is non-zero (for the
1807 // targets ANY_SAMPLES_PASSED_EXT and ANY_SAMPLES_PASSED_CONSERVATIVE_EXT, if
1808 // the active query for either target is non-zero), if <id> is the name of an
1809 // existing query object whose type does not match <target>, or if <id> is the
1810 // active query object name for any query type, the error INVALID_OPERATION is
1811 // generated.
1812
1813 // Ensure no other queries are active
1814 // NOTE: If other queries than occlusion are supported, we will need to check
1815 // separately that:
1816 // a) The query ID passed is not the current active query for any target/type
1817 // b) There are no active queries for the requested target (and in the case
1818 // of GL_ANY_SAMPLES_PASSED_EXT and GL_ANY_SAMPLES_PASSED_CONSERVATIVE_EXT,
1819 // no query may be active for either if glBeginQuery targets either.
1820
1821 if (context->getState().isQueryActive(target))
1822 {
1823 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kOtherQueryActive);
1824 return false;
1825 }
1826
1827 // check that name was obtained with glGenQueries
1828 if (!context->isQueryGenerated(id))
1829 {
1830 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidQueryId);
1831 return false;
1832 }
1833
1834 // Check for type mismatch. If query is not yet started we're good to go.
1835 Query *queryObject = context->getQuery(id);
1836 if (queryObject && queryObject->getType() != target)
1837 {
1838 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kQueryTargetMismatch);
1839 return false;
1840 }
1841
1842 return true;
1843}

1849 {

1919bool ValidateGetQueryivBase(const Context *context,
1920 QueryType target,
1921 GLenum pname,
1922 GLsizei *numParams)
1923{
1924 if (numParams)
1925 {

1929 if (!ValidQueryType(context, target) && target != QueryType::Timestamp)
1930 {
1931 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidQueryType);
1932 return false;

1936 {
1937 case GL_CURRENT_QUERY_EXT:

1949 return false;

1951 break;

1953 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidPname);
1954 return false;

1957 if (numParams)
1958 {
1959 // All queries return only one value
1960 *numParams = 1;
1961 }
1962
1963 return true;

2257
2258bool ValidateUniformCommonBase(const Context *context,
2259 const Program *program,
2260 UniformLocation location,
2261 GLsizei count,
2262 const LinkedUniform **uniformOut)
2263{
2264 // TODO(Jiajia): Add image uniform check in future.
2265 if (count < 0)
2266 {
2267 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kNegativeCount);
2268 return false;
2269 }
2270
2271 if (!program)
2272 {
2273 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidProgramName);
2274 return false;
2275 }
2276
2277 if (!program->isLinked())
2278 {
2279 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kProgramNotLinked);
2280 return false;
2281 }
2282
2283 if (location.value == -1)
2284 {
2285 // Silently ignore the uniform command
2286 return false;
2287 }
2288
2289 const auto &uniformLocations = program->getUniformLocations();
2290 size_t castedLocation = static_cast<size_t>(location.value);
2291 if (castedLocation >= uniformLocations.size())
2292 {
2293 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidUniformLocation);
2294 return false;
2295 }
2296
2297 const auto &uniformLocation = uniformLocations[castedLocation];
2298 if (uniformLocation.ignored)
2299 {
2300 // Silently ignore the uniform command
2301 return false;
2302 }
2303
2304 if (!uniformLocation.used())
2305 {
2306 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidUniformLocation);
2307 return false;
2308 }
2309
2310 const auto &uniform = program->getUniformByIndex(uniformLocation.index);
2311
2312 // attempting to write an array to a non-array uniform is an INVALID_OPERATION
2313 if (count > 1 && !uniform.isArray())
2314 {
2315 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidUniformCount);
2316 return false;
2317 }
2318
2319 *uniformOut = &uniform;
2320 return true;
2321}
2322
2323bool ValidateUniform1ivValue(const Context *context,
2324 GLenum uniformType,
2325 GLsizei count,
2326 const GLint *value)
2327{
2328 // Value type is GL_INT, because we only get here from glUniform1i{v}.
2329 // It is compatible with INT or BOOL.
2330 // Do these cheap tests first, for a little extra speed.
2331 if (GL_INT == uniformType || GL_BOOL == uniformType)
2332 {
2333 return true;
2334 }
2335
2336 if (IsSamplerType(uniformType))
2337 {
2338 // Check that the values are in range.
2339 const GLint max = context->getCaps().maxCombinedTextureImageUnits;
2340 for (GLsizei i = 0; i < count; ++i)
2341 {
2342 if (value[i] < 0 || value[i] >= max)
2343 {
2344 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kSamplerUniformValueOutOfRange);
2345 return false;
2346 }
2347 }
2348 return true;
2349 }
2350
2351 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kUniformTypeMismatch);
2352 return false;
2353}

2357 // Check that the value type is compatible with uniform type.
2358 if (valueType == uniformType)
2359 {
2360 return true;
2361 }
2362
2363 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kUniformTypeMismatch);
2364 return false;
2365}

2406
2407bool ValidateStateQuery(const Context *context,
2408 GLenum pname,
2409 GLenum *nativeType,
2410 unsigned int *numParams)
2411{
2412 if (!context->getQueryParameterInfo(pname, nativeType, numParams))
2413 {
2414 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidPname);
2415 return false;
2416 }
2417
2418 const Caps &caps = context->getCaps();
2419
2420 if (pname >= GL_DRAW_BUFFER0 && pname <= GL_DRAW_BUFFER15)
2421 {
2422 int colorAttachment = (pname - GL_DRAW_BUFFER0);
2423
2424 if (colorAttachment >= caps.maxDrawBuffers)
2425 {
2426 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kIndexExceedsMaxDrawBuffer);
2427 return false;
2428 }
2429 }
2430
2431 switch (pname)
2432 {
2433 case GL_TEXTURE_BINDING_2D:
2434 case GL_TEXTURE_BINDING_CUBE_MAP:
2435 case GL_TEXTURE_BINDING_3D:
2436 case GL_TEXTURE_BINDING_2D_ARRAY:
2437 case GL_TEXTURE_BINDING_2D_MULTISAMPLE:
2438 break;
2439 case GL_TEXTURE_BINDING_2D_MULTISAMPLE_ARRAY:
2440 if (!context->getExtensions().textureStorageMultisample2DArrayOES)
2441 {
2442 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kMultisampleArrayExtensionRequired);
2443 return false;
2444 }
2445 break;
2446 case GL_TEXTURE_BINDING_RECTANGLE_ANGLE:
2447 if (!context->getExtensions().textureRectangle)
2448 {
2449 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
2450 return false;
2451 }
2452 break;
2453 case GL_TEXTURE_BINDING_EXTERNAL_OES:
2454 if (!context->getExtensions().eglStreamConsumerExternalNV &&
2455 !context->getExtensions().eglImageExternalOES)
2456 {
2457 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
2458 return false;
2459 }
2460 break;
2461 case GL_TEXTURE_BUFFER_BINDING:
2462 case GL_TEXTURE_BINDING_BUFFER:
2463 case GL_TEXTURE_BUFFER_OFFSET_ALIGNMENT:
2464 case GL_MAX_TEXTURE_BUFFER_SIZE:
2465 if (context->getClientVersion() < Version(3, 2) &&
2466 !context->getExtensions().textureBufferAny())
2467 {
2468 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kTextureBufferExtensionNotAvailable);
2469 return false;
2470 }
2471 break;
2472
2473 case GL_IMPLEMENTATION_COLOR_READ_TYPE:
2474 case GL_IMPLEMENTATION_COLOR_READ_FORMAT:
2475 {
2476 Framebuffer *readFramebuffer = context->getState().getReadFramebuffer();
2477 ASSERT(readFramebuffer);
2478
2479 if (!ValidateFramebufferComplete<GL_INVALID_OPERATION>(context, readFramebuffer))
2480 {
2481 return false;
2482 }
2483
2484 if (readFramebuffer->getReadBufferState() == GL_NONE)
2485 {
2486 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kReadBufferNone);
2487 return false;
2488 }
2489
2490 const FramebufferAttachment *attachment = readFramebuffer->getReadColorAttachment();
2491 if (!attachment)
2492 {
2493 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kReadBufferNotAttached);
2494 return false;
2495 }
2496 }
2497 break;
2498
2499 default:
2500 break;
2501 }
2502
2503 // pname is valid, but there are no parameters to return
2504 if (*numParams == 0)
2505 {
2506 return false;
2507 }
2508
2509 return true;
2510}

2616
2617bool ValidateCopyImageSubDataTarget(const Context *context, GLuint name, GLenum target)
2618{
2619 // From EXT_copy_image: INVALID_ENUM is generated if either <srcTarget> or <dstTarget> is not
2620 // RENDERBUFFER or a valid non - proxy texture target, is TEXTURE_BUFFER, or is one of the
2621 // cubemap face selectors described in table 3.17, or if the target does not match the type of
2622 // the object. INVALID_VALUE is generated if either <srcName> or <dstName> does not correspond
2623 // to a valid renderbuffer or texture object according to the corresponding target parameter.
2624 switch (target)
2625 {
2626 case GL_RENDERBUFFER:
2627 {
2628 RenderbufferID renderbuffer = FromGL<RenderbufferID>(name);
2629 if (!context->isRenderbuffer(renderbuffer))
2630 {
2631 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidRenderbufferName);
2632 return false;
2633 }
2634 break;
2635 }
2636 case GL_TEXTURE_2D:
2637 case GL_TEXTURE_3D:
2638 case GL_TEXTURE_2D_ARRAY:
2639 case GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP:
2640 case GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_ARRAY_EXT:
2641 {
2642 TextureID texture = FromGL<TextureID>(name);
2643 if (!context->isTexture(texture))
2644 {
2645 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidTextureName);
2646 return false;
2647 }
2648
2649 Texture *textureObject = context->getTexture(texture);
2650 if (textureObject && textureObject->getType() != FromGL<TextureType>(target))
2651 {
2652 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, err::kTextureTypeMismatch);
2653 return false;
2654 }
2655 break;
2656 }
2657 default:
2658 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidTarget);
2659 return false;
2660 }
2661
2662 return true;
2663}
2664
2665bool ValidateCopyImageSubDataTargetRegion(const Context *context,
2666 GLuint name,
2667 GLenum target,
2668 GLint level,
2669 GLint offsetX,
2670 GLint offsetY,
2671 GLint offsetZ,
2672 GLsizei width,
2673 GLsizei height,
2674 GLsizei *samples)
2675{
2676 // INVALID_VALUE is generated if the dimensions of the either subregion exceeds the boundaries
2677 // of the corresponding image object.
2678 if (offsetX < 0 || offsetY < 0 || offsetZ < 0)
2679 {
2680 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kNegativeOffset);
2681 return false;
2682 }
2683
2684 if (target == GL_RENDERBUFFER)
2685 {
2686 // For renderbuffers, this value must be zero. INVALID_VALUE is generated if the specified
2687 // level is not a valid level for the image.
2688 if (level != 0)
2689 {
2690 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidMipLevel);
2691 return false;
2692 }
2693
2694 // INVALID_VALUE is generated if the dimensions of the either subregion exceeds the
2695 // boundaries of the corresponding image object
2696 Renderbuffer *buffer = context->getRenderbuffer(FromGL<RenderbufferID>(name));
2697 if ((buffer->getWidth() - offsetX < width) || (buffer->getHeight() - offsetY < height))
2698 {
2699 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kSourceTextureTooSmall);
2700 return false;
2701 }
2702 }
2703 else
2704 {
2705 // INVALID_VALUE is generated if the specified level is not a valid level for the image
2706 if (!ValidMipLevel(context, FromGL<TextureType>(target), level))
2707 {
2708 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidMipLevel);
2709 return false;
2710 }
2711
2712 Texture *texture = context->getTexture(FromGL<TextureID>(name));
2713
2714 // INVALID_OPERATION is generated if either object is a texture and the texture is not
2715 // complete
2716 // This will handle the texture completeness check. Note that this is missing
2717 // completeness validation that ignores format-based compleness rules.
2718 if (!texture->isSamplerComplete(context, nullptr))
2719 {
2720 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kNotTextureComplete);
2721 return false;
2722 }
2723
2724 GLenum textureTargetToUse = target;
2725 if (target == GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP)
2726 {
2727 // Use GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_X to properly gather the textureWidth/textureHeight
2728 textureTargetToUse = GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_X;
2729 }
2730
2731 const GLsizei textureWidth = static_cast<GLsizei>(
2732 texture->getWidth(FromGL<TextureTarget>(textureTargetToUse), level));
2733 const GLsizei textureHeight = static_cast<GLsizei>(
2734 texture->getHeight(FromGL<TextureTarget>(textureTargetToUse), level));
2735
2736 // INVALID_VALUE is generated if the dimensions of the either subregion exceeds the
2737 // boundaries of the corresponding image object
2738 if ((textureWidth - offsetX < width) || (textureHeight - offsetY < height))
2739 {
2740 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kSourceTextureTooSmall);
2741 return false;
2742 }
2743
2744 *samples = texture->getSamples(FromGL<TextureTarget>(textureTargetToUse), level);
2745 *samples = (*samples == 0) ? 1 : *samples;
2746 }
2747
2748 return true;
2749}
2750
2751bool ValidateCompressedRegion(const Context *context,
2752 const InternalFormat &formatInfo,
2753 GLsizei width,
2754 GLsizei height)
2755{
2756 if (formatInfo.compressed)
2757 {
2758 // INVALID_VALUE is generated if the image format is compressed and the dimensions of the
2759 // subregion fail to meet the alignment constraints of the format.
2760 if ((width % formatInfo.compressedBlockWidth != 0) ||
2761 (height % formatInfo.compressedBlockHeight != 0))
2762 {
2763 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidCompressedRegionSize);
2764 return false;
2765 }
2766 }
2767
2768 return true;
2769}
2770
2771const InternalFormat &GetTargetFormatInfo(const Context *context,
2772 GLuint name,
2773 GLenum target,
2774 GLint level)
2775{
2776 static const InternalFormat defaultInternalFormat;
2777
2778 switch (target)
2779 {
2780 case GL_RENDERBUFFER:
2781 {
2782 Renderbuffer *buffer = context->getRenderbuffer(FromGL<RenderbufferID>(name));
2783 return *buffer->getFormat().info;
2784 break;
2785 }
2786 case GL_TEXTURE_2D:
2787 case GL_TEXTURE_3D:
2788 case GL_TEXTURE_2D_ARRAY:
2789 case GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP:
2790 case GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_ARRAY_EXT:
2791 {
2792 Texture *texture = context->getTexture(FromGL<TextureID>(name));
2793 GLenum textureTargetToUse = target;
2794
2795 if (target == GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP)
2796 {
2797 // Use GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_X to properly gather the
2798 // textureWidth/textureHeight
2799 textureTargetToUse = GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_X;
2800 }
2801 return *texture->getFormat(FromGL<TextureTarget>(textureTargetToUse), level).info;
2802 }
2803 default:
2804 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidTarget);
2805 return defaultInternalFormat;
2806 }
2807}

2923bool ValidateCopyCompressedFormatCompatible(const InternalFormat &srcFormatInfo,
2924 const InternalFormat &dstFormatInfo)
2925{
2926 // Validates compressed format compatibility from Table 4.X.2 of the EXT_copy_image spec.
2927
2928 ASSERT(srcFormatInfo.internalFormat != dstFormatInfo.internalFormat);
2929
2930 const GLenum srcFormat = srcFormatInfo.internalFormat;
2931 const GLenum dstFormat = dstFormatInfo.internalFormat;
2932
2933 switch (srcFormat)
2934 {
2935 case GL_COMPRESSED_RED_RGTC1_EXT:
2936 return (dstFormat == GL_COMPRESSED_SIGNED_RED_RGTC1_EXT);
2937 case GL_COMPRESSED_SIGNED_RED_RGTC1_EXT:
2938 return (dstFormat == GL_COMPRESSED_RED_RGTC1_EXT);
2939 case GL_COMPRESSED_RED_GREEN_RGTC2_EXT:
2940 return (dstFormat == GL_COMPRESSED_SIGNED_RED_GREEN_RGTC2_EXT);
2941 case GL_COMPRESSED_SIGNED_RED_GREEN_RGTC2_EXT:
2942 return (dstFormat == GL_COMPRESSED_RED_GREEN_RGTC2_EXT);
2943 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB_BPTC_SIGNED_FLOAT_EXT:
2944 return (dstFormat == GL_COMPRESSED_RGB_BPTC_UNSIGNED_FLOAT_EXT);
2945 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB_BPTC_UNSIGNED_FLOAT_EXT:
2946 return (dstFormat == GL_COMPRESSED_RGB_BPTC_SIGNED_FLOAT_EXT);
2947 case GL_COMPRESSED_R11_EAC:
2948 return (dstFormat == GL_COMPRESSED_SIGNED_R11_EAC);
2949 case GL_COMPRESSED_SIGNED_R11_EAC:
2950 return (dstFormat == GL_COMPRESSED_R11_EAC);
2951 case GL_COMPRESSED_RG11_EAC:
2952 return (dstFormat == GL_COMPRESSED_SIGNED_RG11_EAC);
2953 case GL_COMPRESSED_SIGNED_RG11_EAC:
2954 return (dstFormat == GL_COMPRESSED_RG11_EAC);
2955 default:
2956 break;
2957 }
2958
2959 // Since they can't be the same format and are both compressed formats, one must be linear and
2960 // the other nonlinear.
2961 if (srcFormatInfo.colorEncoding == dstFormatInfo.colorEncoding)
2962 {
2963 return false;
2964 }
2965
2966 const GLenum linearFormat = (srcFormatInfo.colorEncoding == GL_LINEAR) ? srcFormat : dstFormat;
2967 const GLenum nonLinearFormat =
2968 (srcFormatInfo.colorEncoding != GL_LINEAR) ? srcFormat : dstFormat;
2969
2970 switch (linearFormat)
2971 {
2972 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_BPTC_UNORM_EXT:

3042
3043bool ValidateCopyFormatCompatible(const InternalFormat &srcFormatInfo,
3044 const InternalFormat &dstFormatInfo)
3045{
3046 // Matching source and destination formats are compatible.
3047 if (srcFormatInfo.internalFormat == dstFormatInfo.internalFormat)
3048 {
3049 return true;
3050 }
3051
3052 if (srcFormatInfo.compressed != dstFormatInfo.compressed)
3053 {
3054 GLenum uncompressedFormat = (!srcFormatInfo.compressed) ? srcFormatInfo.internalFormat
3055 : dstFormatInfo.internalFormat;
3056 GLenum compressedFormat = (srcFormatInfo.compressed) ? srcFormatInfo.internalFormat
3057 : dstFormatInfo.internalFormat;
3058
3059 return ValidateCopyMixedFormatCompatible(uncompressedFormat, compressedFormat);
3060 }
3061
3062 if (!srcFormatInfo.compressed)
3063 {
3064 // Source and destination are uncompressed formats.
3065 return (srcFormatInfo.pixelBytes == dstFormatInfo.pixelBytes);
3066 }
3067
3068 return ValidateCopyCompressedFormatCompatible(srcFormatInfo, dstFormatInfo);
3069}
3070
3071bool ValidateCopyImageSubDataBase(const Context *context,
3072 GLuint srcName,
3073 GLenum srcTarget,
3074 GLint srcLevel,
3075 GLint srcX,
3076 GLint srcY,
3077 GLint srcZ,
3078 GLuint dstName,
3079 GLenum dstTarget,
3080 GLint dstLevel,
3081 GLint dstX,
3082 GLint dstY,
3083 GLint dstZ,
3084 GLsizei srcWidth,
3085 GLsizei srcHeight,
3086 GLsizei srcDepth)
3087{
3088 // INVALID_VALUE is generated if the dimensions of the either subregion exceeds the boundaries
3089 // of the corresponding image object
3090 if ((srcWidth < 0) || (srcHeight < 0) || (srcDepth < 0))
3091 {
3092 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kNegativeSize);
3093 return false;
3094 }
3095
3096 if (!ValidateCopyImageSubDataTarget(context, srcName, srcTarget))
3097 {
3098 return false;
3099 }
3100 if (!ValidateCopyImageSubDataTarget(context, dstName, dstTarget))
3101 {
3102 return false;
3103 }
3104
3105 const InternalFormat &srcFormatInfo =
3106 GetTargetFormatInfo(context, srcName, srcTarget, srcLevel);
3107 const InternalFormat &dstFormatInfo =
3108 GetTargetFormatInfo(context, dstName, dstTarget, dstLevel);
3109 GLsizei dstWidth = srcWidth;
3110 GLsizei dstHeight = srcHeight;
3111 GLsizei srcSamples = 1;
3112 GLsizei dstSamples = 1;
3113
3114 if (!ValidateCopyImageSubDataTargetRegion(context, srcName, srcTarget, srcLevel, srcX, srcY,
3115 srcZ, srcWidth, srcHeight, &srcSamples))
3116 {
3117 return false;
3118 }
3119
3120 // When copying from a compressed image to an uncompressed image the image texel dimensions
3121 // written to the uncompressed image will be source extent divided by the compressed texel block
3122 // dimensions.
3123 if ((srcFormatInfo.compressed) && (!dstFormatInfo.compressed))
3124 {
3125 ASSERT(srcFormatInfo.compressedBlockWidth != 0);
3126 ASSERT(srcFormatInfo.compressedBlockHeight != 0);
3127
3128 dstWidth /= srcFormatInfo.compressedBlockWidth;
3129 dstHeight /= srcFormatInfo.compressedBlockHeight;
3130 }
3131 // When copying from an uncompressed image to a compressed image the image texel dimensions
3132 // written to the compressed image will be the source extent multiplied by the compressed texel
3133 // block dimensions.
3134 else if ((!srcFormatInfo.compressed) && (dstFormatInfo.compressed))
3135 {
3136 dstWidth *= dstFormatInfo.compressedBlockWidth;
3137 dstHeight *= dstFormatInfo.compressedBlockHeight;
3138 }
3139
3140 if (!ValidateCopyImageSubDataTargetRegion(context, dstName, dstTarget, dstLevel, dstX, dstY,
3141 dstZ, dstWidth, dstHeight, &dstSamples))
3142 {
3143 return false;
3144 }
3145
3146 if (!ValidateCompressedRegion(context, srcFormatInfo, srcWidth, srcHeight))
3147 {
3148 return false;
3149 }
3150
3151 if (!ValidateCompressedRegion(context, dstFormatInfo, dstWidth, dstHeight))
3152 {
3153 return false;
3154 }
3155
3156 // From EXT_copy_image: INVALID_OPERATION is generated if the source and destination formats
3157 // are not compatible, if one image is compressed and the other is uncompressed and the block
3158 // size of compressed image is not equal to the texel size of the compressed image.
3159 if (!ValidateCopyFormatCompatible(srcFormatInfo, dstFormatInfo))
3160 {
3161 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kIncompatibleTextures);
3162 return false;
3163 }
3164
3165 // INVALID_OPERATION is generated if the source and destination number of samples do not match
3166 if (srcSamples != dstSamples)
3167 {
3168 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kSamplesOutOfRange);
3169 return false;
3170 }
3171
3172 return true;
3173}
3174
3175bool ValidateCopyTexImageParametersBase(const Context *context,
3176 TextureTarget target,
3177 GLint level,
3178 GLenum internalformat,
3179 bool isSubImage,
3180 GLint xoffset,
3181 GLint yoffset,
3182 GLint zoffset,
3183 GLint x,
3184 GLint y,
3185 GLsizei width,
3186 GLsizei height,
3187 GLint border,
3188 Format *textureFormatOut)
3189{
3190 TextureType texType = TextureTargetToType(target);
3191
3192 if (xoffset < 0 || yoffset < 0 || zoffset < 0)
3193 {
3194 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kNegativeOffset);
3195 return false;
3196 }
3197
3198 if (width < 0 || height < 0)
3199 {
3200 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kNegativeSize);
3201 return false;
3202 }
3203
3204 if (std::numeric_limits<GLsizei>::max() - xoffset < width ||
3205 std::numeric_limits<GLsizei>::max() - yoffset < height)
3206 {
3207 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kOffsetOverflow);
3208 return false;
3209 }
3210
3211 if (border != 0)
3212 {
3213 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidBorder);
3214 return false;
3215 }
3216
3217 if (!ValidMipLevel(context, texType, level))
3218 {
3219 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidMipLevel);
3220 return false;
3221 }
3222
3223 const State &state = context->getState();
3224 Framebuffer *readFramebuffer = state.getReadFramebuffer();
3225 if (!ValidateFramebufferComplete(context, readFramebuffer))
3226 {
3227 return false;
3228 }
3229
3230 // checkReadBufferResourceSamples = true. Treat renderToTexture textures as single sample since
3231 // they will be resolved before copying.
3232 if (!readFramebuffer->isDefault() &&
3233 !ValidateFramebufferNotMultisampled(context, readFramebuffer, true))
3234 {
3235 return false;
3236 }
3237
3238 if (readFramebuffer->getReadBufferState() == GL_NONE)
3239 {
3240 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kReadBufferNone);
3241 return false;
3242 }
3243
3244 // WebGL 1.0 [Section 6.26] Reading From a Missing Attachment
3245 // In OpenGL ES it is undefined what happens when an operation tries to read from a missing
3246 // attachment and WebGL defines it to be an error. We do the check unconditionally as the
3247 // situation is an application error that would lead to a crash in ANGLE.
3248 const FramebufferAttachment *source = readFramebuffer->getReadColorAttachment();
3249 if (source == nullptr)
3250 {
3251 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kMissingReadAttachment);
3252 return false;
3253 }
3254
3255 // ANGLE_multiview spec, Revision 1:
3256 // Calling CopyTexSubImage3D, CopyTexImage2D, or CopyTexSubImage2D will result in an
3257 // INVALID_FRAMEBUFFER_OPERATION error if the multi-view layout of the current read framebuffer
3258 // is FRAMEBUFFER_MULTIVIEW_SIDE_BY_SIDE_ANGLE or the number of views in the current read
3259 // framebuffer is more than one.
3260 if (readFramebuffer->readDisallowedByMultiview())
3261 {
3262 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_FRAMEBUFFER_OPERATION, kMultiviewReadFramebuffer);
3263 return false;
3264 }
3265
3266 const Caps &caps = context->getCaps();
3267
3268 GLint maxDimension = 0;
3269 switch (texType)
3270 {
3271 case TextureType::_2D:
3272 maxDimension = caps.max2DTextureSize;
3273 break;
3274
3275 case TextureType::CubeMap:
3276 case TextureType::CubeMapArray:
3277 maxDimension = caps.maxCubeMapTextureSize;
3278 break;
3279
3280 case TextureType::Rectangle:
3281 maxDimension = caps.maxRectangleTextureSize;
3282 break;
3283
3284 case TextureType::_2DArray:
3285 maxDimension = caps.max2DTextureSize;
3286 break;
3287
3288 case TextureType::_3D:
3289 maxDimension = caps.max3DTextureSize;
3290 break;
3291
3292 default:
3293 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidTextureTarget);
3294 return false;
3295 }
3296
3297 Texture *texture = state.getTargetTexture(texType);
3298 if (!texture)
3299 {
3300 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kTextureNotBound);
3301 return false;
3302 }
3303
3304 if (texture->getImmutableFormat() && !isSubImage)
3305 {
3306 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kTextureIsImmutable);
3307 return false;
3308 }
3309
3310 const InternalFormat &formatInfo =
3311 isSubImage ? *texture->getFormat(target, level).info
3312 : GetInternalFormatInfo(internalformat, GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE);
3313
3314 if (formatInfo.depthBits > 0 || formatInfo.compressed)
3315 {
3316 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
3317 return false;
3318 }
3319
3320 if (isSubImage)
3321 {
3322 if (static_cast<size_t>(xoffset + width) > texture->getWidth(target, level) ||
3323 static_cast<size_t>(yoffset + height) > texture->getHeight(target, level) ||
3324 static_cast<size_t>(zoffset) >= texture->getDepth(target, level))
3325 {
3326 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kOffsetOverflow);
3327 return false;
3328 }
3329 }
3330 else
3331 {
3332 if ((texType == TextureType::CubeMap || texType == TextureType::CubeMapArray) &&
3333 width != height)
3334 {
3335 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kCubemapIncomplete);
3336 return false;
3337 }
3338
3339 if (!formatInfo.textureSupport(context->getClientVersion(), context->getExtensions()))
3340 {
3341 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
3342 return false;
3343 }
3344
3345 int maxLevelDimension = (maxDimension >> level);
3346 if (static_cast<int>(width) > maxLevelDimension ||
3347 static_cast<int>(height) > maxLevelDimension)
3348 {
3349 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kResourceMaxTextureSize);
3350 return false;
3351 }
3352 }
3353
3354 if (textureFormatOut)
3355 {
3356 *textureFormatOut = texture->getFormat(target, level);
3357 }
3358
3359 // Detect texture copying feedback loops for WebGL.
3360 if (context->getExtensions().webglCompatibility)
3361 {
3362 if (readFramebuffer->formsCopyingFeedbackLoopWith(texture->id(), level, zoffset))
3363 {
3364 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kFeedbackLoop);
3365 return false;
3366 }
3367 }
3368
3369 return true;
3370}
