3372const char *ValidateProgramPipelineDrawStates(const State &state,
3373 const Extensions &extensions,
3374 ProgramPipeline *programPipeline)
3375{
3376 for (const ShaderType shaderType : gl::AllShaderTypes())
3377 {
3378 Program *program = programPipeline->getShaderProgram(shaderType);
3379 if (program)
3380 {
3381 const char *errorMsg = ValidateProgramDrawStates(state, extensions, program);
3382 if (errorMsg)
3383 {
3384 return errorMsg;
3385 }
3386 }
3387 }
3388
3389 return nullptr;
3390}
3391
3392const char *ValidateProgramPipelineAttachedPrograms(ProgramPipeline *programPipeline)
3393{
3394 // An INVALID_OPERATION error is generated by any command that transfers vertices to the
3395 // GL or launches compute work if the current set of active
3396 // program objects cannot be executed, for reasons including:
3397 // - A program object is active for at least one, but not all of the shader
3398 // stages that were present when the program was linked.
3399 for (const ShaderType shaderType : gl::AllShaderTypes())
3400 {
3401 Program *shaderProgram = programPipeline->getShaderProgram(shaderType);
3402 if (shaderProgram)
3403 {
3404 ProgramExecutable &executable = shaderProgram->getExecutable();
3405 for (const ShaderType programShaderType : executable.getLinkedShaderStages())
3406 {
3407 if (shaderProgram != programPipeline->getShaderProgram(programShaderType))
3408 {
3409 return gl::err::kNotAllStagesOfSeparableProgramUsed;
3410 }
3411 }
3412 }
3413 }
3414
3415 return nullptr;
3416}
3417
3418// Note all errors returned from this function are INVALID_OPERATION except for the draw framebuffer
3419// completeness check.
3420const char *ValidateDrawStates(const Context *context)
3421{
3422 const Extensions &extensions = context->getExtensions();
3423 const State &state = context->getState();
3424
3425 // WebGL buffers cannot be mapped/unmapped because the MapBufferRange, FlushMappedBufferRange,
3426 // and UnmapBuffer entry points are removed from the WebGL 2.0 API.
3427 // https://www.khronos.org/registry/webgl/specs/latest/2.0/#5.14
3428 VertexArray *vertexArray = state.getVertexArray();
3429 ASSERT(vertexArray);
3430
3431 if (!extensions.webglCompatibility && vertexArray->hasMappedEnabledArrayBuffer())
3432 {
3433 return kBufferMapped;
3434 }
3435
3436 // Note: these separate values are not supported in WebGL, due to D3D's limitations. See
3437 // Section 6.10 of the WebGL 1.0 spec.
3438 Framebuffer *framebuffer = state.getDrawFramebuffer();
3439 ASSERT(framebuffer);
3440
3441 if (context->getLimitations().noSeparateStencilRefsAndMasks || extensions.webglCompatibility)
3442 {
3443 ASSERT(framebuffer);
3444 const FramebufferAttachment *dsAttachment =
3445 framebuffer->getStencilOrDepthStencilAttachment();
3446 const GLuint stencilBits = dsAttachment ? dsAttachment->getStencilSize() : 0;
3447 ASSERT(stencilBits <= 8);
3448
3449 const DepthStencilState &depthStencilState = state.getDepthStencilState();
3450 if (depthStencilState.stencilTest && stencilBits > 0)
3451 {
3452 GLuint maxStencilValue = (1 << stencilBits) - 1;
3453
3454 bool differentRefs =
3455 clamp(state.getStencilRef(), 0, static_cast<GLint>(maxStencilValue)) !=
3456 clamp(state.getStencilBackRef(), 0, static_cast<GLint>(maxStencilValue));
3457 bool differentWritemasks = (depthStencilState.stencilWritemask & maxStencilValue) !=
3458 (depthStencilState.stencilBackWritemask & maxStencilValue);
3459 bool differentMasks = (depthStencilState.stencilMask & maxStencilValue) !=
3460 (depthStencilState.stencilBackMask & maxStencilValue);
3461
3462 if (differentRefs || differentWritemasks || differentMasks)
3463 {
3464 if (!extensions.webglCompatibility)
3465 {
3466 WARN() << "This ANGLE implementation does not support separate front/back "
3467 "stencil writemasks, reference values, or stencil mask values.";
3468 }
3469 return kStencilReferenceMaskOrMismatch;
3470 }
3471 }
3472 }
3473
3474 if (!extensions.floatBlend)
3475 {
3476 const DrawBufferMask blendEnabledActiveFloat32ColorAttachmentDrawBufferMask =
3477 state.getBlendEnabledDrawBufferMask() &
3478 framebuffer->getActiveFloat32ColorAttachmentDrawBufferMask();
3479 if (blendEnabledActiveFloat32ColorAttachmentDrawBufferMask.any())
3480 {
3481 return kUnsupportedFloatBlending;
3482 }
3483 }
3484
3485 if (context->getLimitations().noSimultaneousConstantColorAndAlphaBlendFunc ||
3486 extensions.webglCompatibility)
3487 {
3488 if (state.hasSimultaneousConstantColorAndAlphaBlendFunc())
3489 {
3490 if (extensions.webglCompatibility)
3491 {
3492 return kInvalidConstantColor;
3493 }
3494
3495 WARN() << kConstantColorAlphaLimitation;
3496 return kConstantColorAlphaLimitation;
3497 }
3498 }
3499
3500 if (!framebuffer->isComplete(context))
3501 {
3502 // Note: this error should be generated as INVALID_FRAMEBUFFER_OPERATION.
3503 return kDrawFramebufferIncomplete;
3504 }
3505
3506 if (context->getStateCache().hasAnyEnabledClientAttrib())
3507 {
3508 if (extensions.webglCompatibility || !state.areClientArraysEnabled())
3509 {
3510 // [WebGL 1.0] Section 6.5 Enabled Vertex Attributes and Range Checking
3511 // If a vertex attribute is enabled as an array via enableVertexAttribArray but no
3512 // buffer is bound to that attribute via bindBuffer and vertexAttribPointer, then calls
3513 // to drawArrays or drawElements will generate an INVALID_OPERATION error.
3514 return kVertexArrayNoBuffer;
3515 }
3516
3517 if (state.getVertexArray()->hasEnabledNullPointerClientArray())
3518 {
3519 // This is an application error that would normally result in a crash, but we catch it
3520 // and return an error
3521 return kVertexArrayNoBufferPointer;
3522 }
3523 }
3524
3525 // If we are running GLES1, there is no current program.
3526 if (context->getClientVersion() >= Version(2, 0))
3527 {
3528 Program *program = state.getLinkedProgram(context);
3529 ProgramPipeline *programPipeline = state.getProgramPipeline();
3530
3531 if (program)
3532 {
3533 if (!program->validateSamplers(nullptr, context->getCaps()))
3534 {
3535 return kTextureTypeConflict;
3536 }
3537
3538 const char *errorMsg = ValidateProgramDrawStates(state, extensions, program);
3539 if (errorMsg)
3540 {
3541 return errorMsg;
3542 }
3543 }
3544 else if (programPipeline)
3545 {
3546 const char *errorMsg = ValidateProgramPipelineAttachedPrograms(programPipeline);
3547 if (errorMsg)
3548 {
3549 return errorMsg;
3550 }
3551
3552 if (!programPipeline->validateSamplers(nullptr, context->getCaps()))
3553 {
3554 return kTextureTypeConflict;
3555 }
3556
3557 errorMsg = ValidateProgramPipelineDrawStates(state, extensions, programPipeline);
3558 if (errorMsg)
3559 {
3560 return errorMsg;
3561 }
3562
3563 bool goodResult = programPipeline->link(context) == angle::Result::Continue;
3564
3565 // If there is no active program for the vertex or fragment shader stages, the results
3566 // of vertex and fragment shader execution will respectively be undefined. However,
3567 // this is not an error, so ANGLE only signals PPO link failures if both VS and FS
3568 // stages are present.
3569 const ProgramExecutable &executable = programPipeline->getExecutable();
3570 if (!goodResult && executable.hasVertexAndFragmentShader())
3571 {
3572 return err::kProgramPipelineLinkFailed;
3573 }
3574 }
3575
3576 // Do some additional WebGL-specific validation
3577 if (extensions.webglCompatibility)
3578 {
3579 if (!state.validateSamplerFormats())
3580 {
3581 return kSamplerFormatMismatch;
3582 }
3583
3584 const TransformFeedback *transformFeedbackObject = state.getCurrentTransformFeedback();
3585 if (state.isTransformFeedbackActive() &&
3586 transformFeedbackObject->buffersBoundForOtherUse())
3587 {
3588 return kTransformFeedbackBufferDoubleBound;
3589 }
3590
3591 // Detect rendering feedback loops for WebGL.
3592 if (framebuffer->formsRenderingFeedbackLoopWith(context))
3593 {
3594 return kFeedbackLoop;
3595 }
3596
3597 // Detect that the vertex shader input types match the attribute types
3598 if (!ValidateVertexShaderAttributeTypeMatch(context))
3599 {
3600 return kVertexShaderTypeMismatch;
3601 }
3602
3603 if (!context->getState().getRasterizerState().rasterizerDiscard &&
3604 !context->getState().allActiveDrawBufferChannelsMasked())
3605 {
3606 // Detect that if there's active color buffer without fragment shader output
3607 if (!ValidateFragmentShaderColorBufferMaskMatch(context))
3608 {
3609 return kDrawBufferMaskMismatch;
3610 }
3611
3612 // Detect that the color buffer types match the fragment shader output types
3613 if (!ValidateFragmentShaderColorBufferTypeMatch(context))
3614 {
3615 return kDrawBufferTypeMismatch;
3616 }
3617 }
3618
3619 const VertexArray *vao = context->getState().getVertexArray();
3620 if (vao->hasTransformFeedbackBindingConflict(context))
3621 {
3622 return kVertexBufferBoundForTransformFeedback;
3623 }
3624 }
3625 }
3626
3627 return nullptr;
3628}
3629
3630void RecordDrawModeError(const Context *context, PrimitiveMode mode)
3631{
3632 const State &state = context->getState();
3633 TransformFeedback *curTransformFeedback = state.getCurrentTransformFeedback();
3634 if (state.isTransformFeedbackActiveUnpaused())
3635 {
3636 if (!ValidateTransformFeedbackPrimitiveMode(context,
3637 curTransformFeedback->getPrimitiveMode(), mode))
3638 {
3639 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidDrawModeTransformFeedback);
3640 return;
3641 }
3642 }
3643
3644 const Extensions &extensions = context->getExtensions();
3645
3646 switch (mode)
3647 {
3648 case PrimitiveMode::Points:
3649 case PrimitiveMode::Lines:
3650 case PrimitiveMode::LineLoop:
3651 case PrimitiveMode::LineStrip:
3652 case PrimitiveMode::Triangles:
3653 case PrimitiveMode::TriangleStrip:
3654 case PrimitiveMode::TriangleFan:
3655 break;
3656
3657 case PrimitiveMode::LinesAdjacency:
3658 case PrimitiveMode::LineStripAdjacency:
3659 case PrimitiveMode::TrianglesAdjacency:
3660 case PrimitiveMode::TriangleStripAdjacency:
3661 if (!extensions.geometryShader)
3662 {
3663 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kGeometryShaderExtensionNotEnabled);
3664 return;
3665 }
3666 break;
3667 default:
3668 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidDrawMode);
3669 return;
3670 }
3671
3672 // If we are running GLES1, there is no current program.
3673 if (context->getClientVersion() >= Version(2, 0))
3674 {
3675 Program *program = context->getActiveLinkedProgram();
3676 ASSERT(program);
3677
3678 // Do geometry shader specific validations
3679 if (program->getExecutable().hasLinkedShaderStage(ShaderType::Geometry))
3680 {
3681 if (!IsCompatibleDrawModeWithGeometryShader(
3682 mode, program->getGeometryShaderInputPrimitiveType()))
3683 {
3684 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION,
3685 kIncompatibleDrawModeAgainstGeometryShader);
3686 return;
3687 }
3688 }
3689 }
3690
3691 // An error should be recorded.
3692 UNREACHABLE();
3693}

3734
3735const char *ValidateDrawElementsStates(const Context *context)
3736{
3737 const State &state = context->getState();
3738
3739 if (context->getStateCache().isTransformFeedbackActiveUnpaused())
3740 {
3741 // EXT_geometry_shader allows transform feedback to work with all draw commands.
3742 // [EXT_geometry_shader] Section 12.1, "Transform Feedback"
3743 if (!context->getExtensions().geometryShader)
3744 {
3745 // It is an invalid operation to call DrawElements, DrawRangeElements or
3746 // DrawElementsInstanced while transform feedback is active, (3.0.2, section 2.14, pg
3747 // 86)
3748 return kUnsupportedDrawModeForTransformFeedback;
3749 }
3750 }
3751
3752 const VertexArray *vao = state.getVertexArray();
3753 Buffer *elementArrayBuffer = vao->getElementArrayBuffer();
3754
3755 if (elementArrayBuffer)
3756 {
3757 if (context->getExtensions().webglCompatibility)
3758 {
3759 if (elementArrayBuffer->isBoundForTransformFeedbackAndOtherUse())
3760 {
3761 return kElementArrayBufferBoundForTransformFeedback;
3762 }
3763 }
3764 else if (elementArrayBuffer->isMapped())
3765 {
3766 // WebGL buffers cannot be mapped/unmapped because the MapBufferRange,
3767 // FlushMappedBufferRange, and UnmapBuffer entry points are removed from the
3768 // WebGL 2.0 API. https://www.khronos.org/registry/webgl/specs/latest/2.0/#5.14
3769 return kBufferMapped;
3770 }
3771 }
3772 else
3773 {
3774 // [WebGL 1.0] Section 6.2 No Client Side Arrays
3775 // If an indexed draw command (drawElements) is called and no WebGLBuffer is bound to
3776 // the ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER binding point, an INVALID_OPERATION error is generated.
3777 if (!context->getState().areClientArraysEnabled() ||
3778 context->getExtensions().webglCompatibility)
3779 {
3780 return kMustHaveElementArrayBinding;
3781 }
3782 }
3783
3784 return nullptr;
3785}

3906static bool ValidateSizedGetUniform(const Context *context,
3907 ShaderProgramID program,
3908 UniformLocation location,
3909 GLsizei bufSize,
3910 GLsizei *length)
3911{
3912 if (length)
3913 {
3914 *length = 0;
3915 }
3916

3918 {
3919 return false;

3925 return false;

3929 ASSERT(programObject);

4079bool ValidateDiscardFramebufferBase(const Context *context,
4080 GLenum target,
4081 GLsizei numAttachments,
4082 const GLenum *attachments,
4083 bool defaultFramebuffer)
4084{
4085 if (numAttachments < 0)
4086 {
4087 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kNegativeAttachments);
4088 return false;
4089 }
4090
4091 for (GLsizei i = 0; i < numAttachments; ++i)
4092 {
4093 if (attachments[i] >= GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0 && attachments[i] <= GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT31)
4094 {
4095 if (defaultFramebuffer)
4096 {
4097 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kDefaultFramebufferInvalidAttachment);
4098 return false;
4099 }
4100
4101 if (attachments[i] >=
4102 GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0 + static_cast<GLuint>(context->getCaps().maxColorAttachments))
4103 {
4104 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kExceedsMaxColorAttachments);
4105 return false;
4106 }
4107 }
4108 else
4109 {
4110 switch (attachments[i])
4111 {
4112 case GL_DEPTH_ATTACHMENT:
4113 case GL_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT:
4114 case GL_DEPTH_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT:
4115 if (defaultFramebuffer)
4116 {
4117 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM,
4118 kDefaultFramebufferInvalidAttachment);
4119 return false;
4120 }
4121 break;
4122 case GL_COLOR:
4123 case GL_DEPTH:
4124 case GL_STENCIL:
4125 if (!defaultFramebuffer)
4126 {
4127 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM,
4128 kDefaultFramebufferAttachmentOnUserFBO);
4129 return false;
4130 }
4131 break;
4132 default:
4133 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidAttachment);
4134 return false;
4135 }
4136 }
4137 }
4138
4139 return true;
4140}

4367
4368bool ValidateDrawBuffersBase(const Context *context, GLsizei n, const GLenum *bufs)
4369{
4370 // INVALID_VALUE is generated if n is negative or greater than value of MAX_DRAW_BUFFERS
4371 if (n < 0)
4372 {
4373 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kNegativeCount);
4374 return false;
4375 }
4376 if (n > context->getCaps().maxDrawBuffers)
4377 {
4378 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kIndexExceedsMaxDrawBuffer);
4379 return false;
4380 }
4381
4382 ASSERT(context->getState().getDrawFramebuffer());
4383 FramebufferID frameBufferId = context->getState().getDrawFramebuffer()->id();
4384 GLuint maxColorAttachment = GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0_EXT + context->getCaps().maxColorAttachments;
4385
4386 // This should come first before the check for the default frame buffer
4387 // because when we switch to ES3.1+, invalid enums will return INVALID_ENUM
4388 // rather than INVALID_OPERATION
4389 for (int colorAttachment = 0; colorAttachment < n; colorAttachment++)
4390 {
4391 const GLenum attachment = GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0_EXT + colorAttachment;
4392
4393 if (bufs[colorAttachment] != GL_NONE && bufs[colorAttachment] != GL_BACK &&
4394 (bufs[colorAttachment] < GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0 ||
4395 bufs[colorAttachment] > GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT31))
4396 {
4397 // Value in bufs is not NONE, BACK, or GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENTi
4398 // The 3.0.4 spec says to generate GL_INVALID_OPERATION here, but this
4399 // was changed to GL_INVALID_ENUM in 3.1, which dEQP also expects.
4400 // 3.1 is still a bit ambiguous about the error, but future specs are
4401 // expected to clarify that GL_INVALID_ENUM is the correct error.
4402 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidDrawBuffer);
4403 return false;
4404 }
4405 else if (bufs[colorAttachment] >= maxColorAttachment)
4406 {
4407 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kExceedsMaxColorAttachments);
4408 return false;
4409 }
4410 else if (bufs[colorAttachment] != GL_NONE && bufs[colorAttachment] != attachment &&
4411 frameBufferId.value != 0)
4412 {
4413 // INVALID_OPERATION-GL is bound to buffer and ith argument
4414 // is not COLOR_ATTACHMENTi or NONE
4415 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidDrawBufferValue);
4416 return false;
4417 }
4418 }
4419
4420 // INVALID_OPERATION is generated if GL is bound to the default framebuffer
4421 // and n is not 1 or bufs is bound to value other than BACK and NONE
4422 if (frameBufferId.value == 0)
4423 {
4424 if (n != 1)
4425 {
4426 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidDrawBufferCountForDefault);
4427 return false;
4428 }
4429
4430 if (bufs[0] != GL_NONE && bufs[0] != GL_BACK)
4431 {
4432 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kDefaultFramebufferInvalidDrawBuffer);
4433 return false;
4434 }
4435 }
4436
4437 return true;
4438}

4502
4503bool ValidateMapBufferRangeBase(const Context *context,
4504 BufferBinding target,
4505 GLintptr offset,
4506 GLsizeiptr length,
4507 GLbitfield access)
4508{
4509 if (!context->isValidBufferBinding(target))
4510 {
4511 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidBufferTypes);
4512 return false;
4513 }
4514
4515 if (offset < 0)
4516 {
4517 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kNegativeOffset);
4518 return false;
4519 }
4520
4521 if (length < 0)
4522 {
4523 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kNegativeLength);
4524 return false;
4525 }
4526
4527 Buffer *buffer = context->getState().getTargetBuffer(target);
4528
4529 if (!buffer)
4530 {
4531 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBufferNotMappable);
4532 return false;
4533 }
4534
4535 // Check for buffer overflow
4536 CheckedNumeric<size_t> checkedOffset(offset);
4537 auto checkedSize = checkedOffset + length;
4538
4539 if (!checkedSize.IsValid() || checkedSize.ValueOrDie() > static_cast<size_t>(buffer->getSize()))
4540 {
4541 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kMapOutOfRange);
4542 return false;
4543 }
4544
4545 // Check for invalid bits in the mask
4546 constexpr GLbitfield kAllAccessBits =
4547 GL_MAP_READ_BIT | GL_MAP_WRITE_BIT | GL_MAP_INVALIDATE_RANGE_BIT |
4548 GL_MAP_INVALIDATE_BUFFER_BIT | GL_MAP_FLUSH_EXPLICIT_BIT | GL_MAP_UNSYNCHRONIZED_BIT;
4549
4550 if (buffer->isImmutable())
4551 {
4552 // GL_EXT_buffer_storage's additions to glMapBufferRange
4553 constexpr GLbitfield kBufferStorageAccessBits =
4554 kAllAccessBits | GL_MAP_PERSISTENT_BIT_EXT | GL_MAP_COHERENT_BIT_EXT;
4555
4556 if ((access & ~kBufferStorageAccessBits) != 0)
4557 {
4558 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidAccessBits);
4559 return false;
4560 }
4561
4562 // It is invalid if any of bufferStorageMatchedAccessBits bits are included in access,
4563 // but the same bits are not included in the buffer's storage flags
4564 constexpr GLbitfield kBufferStorageMatchedAccessBits = GL_MAP_READ_BIT | GL_MAP_WRITE_BIT |
4565 GL_MAP_PERSISTENT_BIT_EXT |
4566 GL_MAP_COHERENT_BIT_EXT;
4567 GLbitfield accessFlags = access & kBufferStorageMatchedAccessBits;
4568 if ((accessFlags & buffer->getStorageExtUsageFlags()) != accessFlags)
4569 {
4570 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidAccessBits);
4571 return false;
4572 }
4573 }
4574 else if ((access & ~kAllAccessBits) != 0)
4575 {
4576 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidAccessBits);
4577 return false;
4578 }
4579
4580 if (length == 0)
4581 {
4582 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kLengthZero);
4583 return false;
4584 }
4585
4586 if (buffer->isMapped())
4587 {
4588 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBufferAlreadyMapped);
4589 return false;
4590 }
4591
4592 // Check for invalid bit combinations
4593 if ((access & (GL_MAP_READ_BIT | GL_MAP_WRITE_BIT)) == 0)
4594 {
4595 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidAccessBitsReadWrite);
4596 return false;
4597 }
4598
4599 GLbitfield writeOnlyBits =
4600 GL_MAP_INVALIDATE_RANGE_BIT | GL_MAP_INVALIDATE_BUFFER_BIT | GL_MAP_UNSYNCHRONIZED_BIT;
4601
4602 if ((access & GL_MAP_READ_BIT) != 0 && (access & writeOnlyBits) != 0)
4603 {
4604 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidAccessBitsRead);
4605 return false;
4606 }
4607
4608 if ((access & GL_MAP_WRITE_BIT) == 0 && (access & GL_MAP_FLUSH_EXPLICIT_BIT) != 0)
4609 {
4610 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidAccessBitsFlush);
4611 return false;
4612 }
4613
4614 return ValidateMapBufferBase(context, target);
4615}

4617bool ValidateFlushMappedBufferRangeBase(const Context *context,

4622 if (offset < 0)

4706bool ValidateGetFramebufferAttachmentParameterivBase(const Context *context,
4707 GLenum target,
4708 GLenum attachment,
4709 GLenum pname,
4710 GLsizei *numParams)
4711{
4712 if (!ValidFramebufferTarget(context, target))
4713 {
4714 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidFramebufferTarget);
4715 return false;
4716 }
4717
4718 int clientVersion = context->getClientMajorVersion();
4719
4720 switch (pname)
4721 {
4722 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_OBJECT_TYPE:
4723 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_OBJECT_NAME:
4724 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_TEXTURE_LEVEL:
4725 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_FACE:
4726 break;
4727
4728 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_TEXTURE_NUM_VIEWS_OVR:
4729 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_TEXTURE_BASE_VIEW_INDEX_OVR:
4730 if (clientVersion < 3 ||
4731 !(context->getExtensions().multiview || context->getExtensions().multiview2))
4732 {
4733 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
4734 return false;
4735 }
4736 break;
4737
4738 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_TEXTURE_SAMPLES_EXT:
4739 if (!context->getExtensions().multisampledRenderToTexture)
4740 {
4741 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
4742 return false;
4743 }
4744 break;
4745
4746 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_COLOR_ENCODING:
4747 if (clientVersion < 3 && !context->getExtensions().sRGB)
4748 {
4749 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
4750 return false;
4751 }
4752 break;
4753
4754 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_RED_SIZE:
4755 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_GREEN_SIZE:
4756 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_BLUE_SIZE:
4757 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_ALPHA_SIZE:
4758 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_DEPTH_SIZE:
4759 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_STENCIL_SIZE:
4760 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_COMPONENT_TYPE:
4761 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_TEXTURE_LAYER:
4762 if (clientVersion < 3)
4763 {
4764 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kES3Required);
4765 return false;
4766 }
4767 break;
4768
4769 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_LAYERED_EXT:
4770 if (!context->getExtensions().geometryShader)
4771 {
4772 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kGeometryShaderExtensionNotEnabled);
4773 return false;
4774 }
4775 break;
4776
4777 default:
4778 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidPname);
4779 return false;
4780 }
4781
4782 // Determine if the attachment is a valid enum
4783 switch (attachment)
4784 {
4785 case GL_BACK:
4786 case GL_DEPTH:
4787 case GL_STENCIL:
4788 if (clientVersion < 3)
4789 {
4790 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidAttachment);
4791 return false;
4792 }
4793 break;
4794
4795 case GL_DEPTH_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT:
4796 if (clientVersion < 3 && !context->isWebGL1())
4797 {
4798 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidAttachment);
4799 return false;
4800 }
4801 break;
4802
4803 case GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0:
4804 case GL_DEPTH_ATTACHMENT:
4805 case GL_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT:
4806 break;
4807
4808 default:
4809 if ((clientVersion < 3 && !context->getExtensions().drawBuffers) ||
4810 attachment < GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0_EXT ||
4811 (attachment - GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0_EXT) >=
4812 static_cast<GLuint>(context->getCaps().maxColorAttachments))
4813 {
4814 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidAttachment);
4815 return false;
4816 }
4817 break;
4818 }
4819
4820 const Framebuffer *framebuffer = context->getState().getTargetFramebuffer(target);
4821 ASSERT(framebuffer);
4822
4823 if (framebuffer->isDefault())
4824 {
4825 if (clientVersion < 3)
4826 {
4827 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kDefaultFramebufferTarget);
4828 return false;
4829 }
4830
4831 switch (attachment)
4832 {
4833 case GL_BACK:
4834 case GL_DEPTH:
4835 case GL_STENCIL:
4836 break;
4837
4838 default:
4839 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidAttachment);
4840 return false;
4841 }
4842 }
4843 else
4844 {
4845 if (attachment >= GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0_EXT && attachment <= GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT15_EXT)
4846 {
4847 // Valid attachment query
4848 }
4849 else
4850 {
4851 switch (attachment)
4852 {
4853 case GL_DEPTH_ATTACHMENT:
4854 case GL_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT:
4855 break;
4856
4857 case GL_DEPTH_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT:
4858 if (!framebuffer->hasValidDepthStencil() && !context->isWebGL1())
4859 {
4860 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidAttachment);
4861 return false;
4862 }
4863 break;
4864
4865 default:
4866 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidAttachment);
4867 return false;
4868 }
4869 }
4870 }
4871
4872 const FramebufferAttachment *attachmentObject = framebuffer->getAttachment(context, attachment);
4873 if (attachmentObject)
4874 {
4875 ASSERT(attachmentObject->type() == GL_RENDERBUFFER ||
4876 attachmentObject->type() == GL_TEXTURE ||
4877 attachmentObject->type() == GL_FRAMEBUFFER_DEFAULT);
4878
4879 switch (pname)
4880 {
4881 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_OBJECT_NAME:
4882 if (attachmentObject->type() != GL_RENDERBUFFER &&
4883 attachmentObject->type() != GL_TEXTURE)
4884 {
4885 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kFramebufferIncompleteAttachment);
4886 return false;
4887 }
4888 break;
4889
4890 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_TEXTURE_LEVEL:
4891 if (attachmentObject->type() != GL_TEXTURE)
4892 {
4893 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kFramebufferIncompleteAttachment);
4894 return false;
4895 }
4896 break;
4897
4898 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_FACE:
4899 if (attachmentObject->type() != GL_TEXTURE)
4900 {
4901 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kFramebufferIncompleteAttachment);
4902 return false;
4903 }
4904 break;
4905
4906 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_COMPONENT_TYPE:
4907 if (attachment == GL_DEPTH_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT)
4908 {
4909 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidAttachment);
4910 return false;
4911 }
4912 break;
4913
4914 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_TEXTURE_LAYER:
4915 if (attachmentObject->type() != GL_TEXTURE)
4916 {
4917 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kFramebufferIncompleteAttachment);
4918 return false;
4919 }
4920 break;
4921
4922 default:
4923 break;
4924 }
4925 }
4926 else
4927 {
4928 // ES 2.0.25 spec pg 127 states that if the value of FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_OBJECT_TYPE
4929 // is NONE, then querying any other pname will generate INVALID_ENUM.
4930
4931 // ES 3.0.2 spec pg 235 states that if the attachment type is none,
4932 // GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_OBJECT_NAME will return zero and be an
4933 // INVALID_OPERATION for all other pnames
4934
4935 switch (pname)
4936 {
4937 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_OBJECT_TYPE:
4938 break;
4939
4940 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_OBJECT_NAME:
4941 if (clientVersion < 3)
4942 {
4943 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM,
4944 kInvalidFramebufferAttachmentParameter);
4945 return false;
4946 }
4947 break;
4948
4949 default:
4950 if (clientVersion < 3)
4951 {
4952 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM,
4953 kInvalidFramebufferAttachmentParameter);
4954 return false;
4955 }
4956 else
4957 {
4958 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION,
4959 kInvalidFramebufferAttachmentParameter);
4960 return false;
4961 }
4962 }
4963 }
4964
4965 if (numParams)
4966 {
4967 *numParams = 1;
4968 }
4969
4970 return true;
4971}

5060bool ValidateGetProgramivBase(const Context *context,
5061 ShaderProgramID program,
5062 GLenum pname,
5063 GLsizei *numParams)
5064{
5065 // Currently, all GetProgramiv queries return 1 parameter
5066 if (numParams)
5067 {
5068 *numParams = 1;
5069 }
5070
5071 if (context->isContextLost())
5072 {
5073 context->validationError(GL_CONTEXT_LOST, kContextLost);
5074
5075 if (context->getExtensions().parallelShaderCompile && pname == GL_COMPLETION_STATUS_KHR)
5076 {
5077 // Generate an error but still return true, the context still needs to return a
5078 // value in this case.
5079 return true;
5080 }
5081 else
5082 {
5083 return false;
5084 }
5085 }
5086
5087 // Special case for GL_COMPLETION_STATUS_KHR: don't resolve the link. Otherwise resolve it now.
5088 Program *programObject = (pname == GL_COMPLETION_STATUS_KHR)
5089 ? GetValidProgramNoResolve(context, program)
5090 : GetValidProgram(context, program);
5091 if (!programObject)
5092 {
5093 return false;
5094 }
5095
5096 switch (pname)
5097 {
5098 case GL_DELETE_STATUS:
5099 case GL_LINK_STATUS:
5100 case GL_VALIDATE_STATUS:
5101 case GL_INFO_LOG_LENGTH:
5102 case GL_ATTACHED_SHADERS:
5103 case GL_ACTIVE_ATTRIBUTES:
5104 case GL_ACTIVE_ATTRIBUTE_MAX_LENGTH:
5105 case GL_ACTIVE_UNIFORMS:
5106 case GL_ACTIVE_UNIFORM_MAX_LENGTH:
5107 break;
5108
5109 case GL_PROGRAM_BINARY_LENGTH:
5110 if (context->getClientMajorVersion() < 3 &&
5111 !context->getExtensions().getProgramBinaryOES)
5112 {
5113 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
5114 return false;
5115 }
5116 break;
5117
5118 case GL_ACTIVE_UNIFORM_BLOCKS:
5119 case GL_ACTIVE_UNIFORM_BLOCK_MAX_NAME_LENGTH:
5120 case GL_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_BUFFER_MODE:
5121 case GL_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_VARYINGS:
5122 case GL_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_VARYING_MAX_LENGTH:
5123 case GL_PROGRAM_BINARY_RETRIEVABLE_HINT:
5124 if (context->getClientMajorVersion() < 3)
5125 {
5126 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumRequiresGLES30);
5127 return false;
5128 }
5129 break;
5130
5131 case GL_PROGRAM_SEPARABLE:
5132 case GL_ACTIVE_ATOMIC_COUNTER_BUFFERS:
5133 if (context->getClientVersion() < Version(3, 1))
5134 {
5135 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumRequiresGLES31);
5136 return false;
5137 }
5138 break;
5139
5140 case GL_COMPUTE_WORK_GROUP_SIZE:
5141 if (context->getClientVersion() < Version(3, 1))
5142 {
5143 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumRequiresGLES31);
5144 return false;
5145 }
5146
5147 // [OpenGL ES 3.1] Chapter 7.12 Page 122
5148 // An INVALID_OPERATION error is generated if COMPUTE_WORK_GROUP_SIZE is queried for a
5149 // program which has not been linked successfully, or which does not contain objects to
5150 // form a compute shader.
5151 if (!programObject->isLinked())
5152 {
5153 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kProgramNotLinked);
5154 return false;
5155 }
5156 if (!programObject->getExecutable().hasLinkedShaderStage(ShaderType::Compute))
5157 {
5158 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kNoActiveComputeShaderStage);
5159 return false;
5160 }
5161 break;
5162
5163 case GL_GEOMETRY_LINKED_INPUT_TYPE_EXT:
5164 case GL_GEOMETRY_LINKED_OUTPUT_TYPE_EXT:
5165 case GL_GEOMETRY_LINKED_VERTICES_OUT_EXT:
5166 case GL_GEOMETRY_SHADER_INVOCATIONS_EXT:
5167 if (!context->getExtensions().geometryShader)
5168 {
5169 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kGeometryShaderExtensionNotEnabled);
5170 return false;
5171 }
5172
5173 // [EXT_geometry_shader] Chapter 7.12
5174 // An INVALID_OPERATION error is generated if GEOMETRY_LINKED_VERTICES_OUT_EXT,
5175 // GEOMETRY_LINKED_INPUT_TYPE_EXT, GEOMETRY_LINKED_OUTPUT_TYPE_EXT, or
5176 // GEOMETRY_SHADER_INVOCATIONS_EXT are queried for a program which has not been linked
5177 // successfully, or which does not contain objects to form a geometry shader.
5178 if (!programObject->isLinked())
5179 {
5180 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kProgramNotLinked);
5181 return false;
5182 }
5183 if (!programObject->getExecutable().hasLinkedShaderStage(ShaderType::Geometry))
5184 {

5186 return false;
5187 }

5189
5190 case GL_COMPLETION_STATUS_KHR:

5192 {
5193 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kExtensionNotEnabled);
5194 return false;
5195 }
5196 break;
5197
5198 default:
5199 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
5200 return false;
5201 }
5202
5203 return true;
5204}

5751// Perform validation from WebGL 2 section 5.10 "Invalid Clears":
5752// In the WebGL 2 API, trying to perform a clear when there is a mismatch between the type of the
5753// specified clear value and the type of a buffer that is being cleared generates an
5754// INVALID_OPERATION error instead of producing undefined results
5755bool ValidateWebGLFramebufferAttachmentClearType(const Context *context,
5756 GLint drawbuffer,
5757 const GLenum *validComponentTypes,
5758 size_t validComponentTypeCount)
5759{
5760 const FramebufferAttachment *attachment =
5761 context->getState().getDrawFramebuffer()->getDrawBuffer(drawbuffer);
5762 if (attachment)
5763 {
5764 GLenum componentType = attachment->getFormat().info->componentType;
5765 const GLenum *end = validComponentTypes + validComponentTypeCount;
5766 if (std::find(validComponentTypes, end, componentType) == end)
5767 {
5768 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kNoDefinedClearConversion);
5769 return false;
5770 }
5771 }
5772
5773 return true;
5774}

5776bool ValidateRobustCompressedTexImageBase(const Context *context,
5777 GLsizei imageSize,
5778 GLsizei dataSize)
5779{
5780 if (!ValidateRobustEntryPoint(context, dataSize))
5781 {
5782 return false;
5783 }
5784
5785 Buffer *pixelUnpackBuffer = context->getState().getTargetBuffer(BufferBinding::PixelUnpack);
5786 if (pixelUnpackBuffer == nullptr)
5787 {
5788 if (dataSize < imageSize)
5789 {
5790 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kCompressedDataSizeTooSmall);
5791 }
5792 }
5793 return true;
5794}
5795
5796bool ValidateGetBufferParameterBase(const Context *context,
5797 BufferBinding target,
5798 GLenum pname,
5799 bool pointerVersion,
5800 GLsizei *numParams)
5801{
5802 if (numParams)
5803 {
5804 *numParams = 0;
5805 }
5806
5807 if (!context->isValidBufferBinding(target))
5808 {
5809 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidBufferTypes);
5810 return false;
5811 }
5812
5813 const Buffer *buffer = context->getState().getTargetBuffer(target);
5814 if (!buffer)
5815 {
5816 // A null buffer means that "0" is bound to the requested buffer target
5817 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBufferNotBound);
5818 return false;
5819 }
5820
5821 const Extensions &extensions = context->getExtensions();
5822
5823 switch (pname)
5824 {
5825 case GL_BUFFER_USAGE:
5826 case GL_BUFFER_SIZE:
5827 break;
5828
5829 case GL_BUFFER_ACCESS_OES:
5830 if (!extensions.mapBufferOES)
5831 {
5832 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
5833 return false;
5834 }
5835 break;
5836
5837 case GL_BUFFER_MAPPED:
5838 static_assert(GL_BUFFER_MAPPED == GL_BUFFER_MAPPED_OES, "GL enums should be equal.");
5839 if (context->getClientMajorVersion() < 3 && !extensions.mapBufferOES &&
5840 !extensions.mapBufferRange)
5841 {
5842 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
5843 return false;
5844 }
5845 break;
5846
5847 case GL_BUFFER_MAP_POINTER:
5848 if (!pointerVersion)
5849 {
5850 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidMapPointerQuery);
5851 return false;
5852 }
5853 break;
5854
5855 case GL_BUFFER_ACCESS_FLAGS:
5856 case GL_BUFFER_MAP_OFFSET:
5857 case GL_BUFFER_MAP_LENGTH:
5858 if (context->getClientMajorVersion() < 3 && !extensions.mapBufferRange)
5859 {
5860 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
5861 return false;
5862 }
5863 break;
5864
5865 case GL_MEMORY_SIZE_ANGLE:
5866 if (!context->getExtensions().memorySize)
5867 {
5868 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kExtensionNotEnabled);
5869 return false;
5870 }
5871 break;
5872
5873 case GL_RESOURCE_INITIALIZED_ANGLE:
5874 if (!context->getExtensions().robustResourceInitialization)
5875 {
5876 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM,
5877 kRobustResourceInitializationExtensionRequired);
5878 return false;
5879 }
5880 break;
5881
5882 default:
5883 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
5884 return false;
5885 }
5886
5887 // All buffer parameter queries return one value.
5888 if (numParams)
5889 {
5890 *numParams = 1;
5891 }
5892
5893 return true;
5894}

5896bool ValidateGetRenderbufferParameterivBase(const Context *context,
5897 GLenum target,
5898 GLenum pname,
5899 GLsizei *length)
5900{
5901 if (length)
5902 {
5903 *length = 0;
5904 }
5905
5906 if (target != GL_RENDERBUFFER)
5907 {
5908 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidRenderbufferTarget);
5909 return false;
5910 }
5911
5912 Renderbuffer *renderbuffer = context->getState().getCurrentRenderbuffer();
5913 if (renderbuffer == nullptr)
5914 {
5915 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kRenderbufferNotBound);
5916 return false;
5917 }
5918
5919 switch (pname)
5920 {
5921 case GL_RENDERBUFFER_WIDTH:
5922 case GL_RENDERBUFFER_HEIGHT:
5923 case GL_RENDERBUFFER_INTERNAL_FORMAT:
5924 case GL_RENDERBUFFER_RED_SIZE:
5925 case GL_RENDERBUFFER_GREEN_SIZE:
5926 case GL_RENDERBUFFER_BLUE_SIZE:
5927 case GL_RENDERBUFFER_ALPHA_SIZE:
5928 case GL_RENDERBUFFER_DEPTH_SIZE:
5929 case GL_RENDERBUFFER_STENCIL_SIZE:
5930 break;
5931
5932 case GL_RENDERBUFFER_SAMPLES_ANGLE:
5933 if (!context->getExtensions().framebufferMultisample)
5934 {
5935 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kExtensionNotEnabled);
5936 return false;
5937 }
5938 break;
5939
5940 case GL_MEMORY_SIZE_ANGLE:
5941 if (!context->getExtensions().memorySize)
5942 {
5943 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kExtensionNotEnabled);
5944 return false;
5945 }
5946 break;
5947
5948 case GL_IMPLEMENTATION_COLOR_READ_FORMAT:
5949 case GL_IMPLEMENTATION_COLOR_READ_TYPE:
5950 if (!context->getExtensions().getImageANGLE)
5951 {
5952 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kGetImageExtensionNotEnabled);
5953 return false;
5954 }
5955 break;
5956
5957 case GL_RESOURCE_INITIALIZED_ANGLE:
5958 if (!context->getExtensions().robustResourceInitialization)
5959 {
5960 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM,
5961 kRobustResourceInitializationExtensionRequired);
5962 return false;
5963 }
5964 break;
5965
5966 default:
5967 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
5968 return false;
5969 }
5970
5971 if (length)
5972 {
5973 *length = 1;
5974 }
5975 return true;
5976}

5978bool ValidateGetShaderivBase(const Context *context,
5979 ShaderProgramID shader,
5980 GLenum pname,
5981 GLsizei *length)
5982{
5983 if (length)
5984 {
5985 *length = 0;
5986 }
5987
5988 if (context->isContextLost())
5989 {
5990 context->validationError(GL_CONTEXT_LOST, kContextLost);
5991
5992 if (context->getExtensions().parallelShaderCompile && pname == GL_COMPLETION_STATUS_KHR)
5993 {
5994 // Generate an error but still return true, the context still needs to return a
5995 // value in this case.
5996 return true;
5997 }
5998 else
5999 {
6000 return false;
6001 }
6002 }
6003
6004 if (GetValidShader(context, shader) == nullptr)
6005 {
6006 return false;
6007 }
6008
6009 switch (pname)
6010 {
6011 case GL_SHADER_TYPE:
6012 case GL_DELETE_STATUS:
6013 case GL_COMPILE_STATUS:
6014 case GL_INFO_LOG_LENGTH:
6015 case GL_SHADER_SOURCE_LENGTH:
6016 break;
6017
6018 case GL_TRANSLATED_SHADER_SOURCE_LENGTH_ANGLE:
6019 if (!context->getExtensions().translatedShaderSource)
6020 {
6021 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kExtensionNotEnabled);
6022 return false;
6023 }
6024 break;
6025
6026 case GL_COMPLETION_STATUS_KHR:
6027 if (!context->getExtensions().parallelShaderCompile)
6028 {
6029 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kExtensionNotEnabled);
6030 return false;
6031 }
6032 break;
6033
6034 default:
6035 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
6036 return false;
6037 }
6038
6039 if (length)
6040 {
6041 *length = 1;
6042 }
6043 return true;
6044}

6046bool ValidateGetTexParameterBase(const Context *context,
6047 TextureType target,
6048 GLenum pname,
6049 GLsizei *length)
6050{
6051 if (length)
6052 {
6053 *length = 0;
6054 }
6055
6056 if (!ValidTextureTarget(context, target) && !ValidTextureExternalTarget(context, target))
6057 {
6058 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidTextureTarget);
6059 return false;
6060 }

6111 case GL_TEXTURE_SWIZZLE_A:

6214bool ValidateGetVertexAttribBase(const Context *context,
6215 GLuint index,
6216 GLenum pname,
6217 GLsizei *length,
6218 bool pointer,
6219 bool pureIntegerEntryPoint)
6220{
6221 if (length)
6222 {
6223 *length = 0;
6224 }
6225
6226 if (pureIntegerEntryPoint && context->getClientMajorVersion() < 3)
6227 {
6228 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kES3Required);
6229 return false;
6230 }
6231
6232 if (index >= static_cast<GLuint>(context->getCaps().maxVertexAttributes))
6233 {
6234 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kIndexExceedsMaxVertexAttribute);
6235 return false;
6236 }
6237
6238 if (pointer)
6239 {
6240 if (pname != GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_POINTER)
6241 {
6242 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
6243 return false;
6244 }
6245 }
6246 else
6247 {
6248 switch (pname)
6249 {
6250 case GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_ENABLED:
6251 case GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_SIZE:
6252 case GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_STRIDE:
6253 case GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_TYPE:
6254 case GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_NORMALIZED:
6255 case GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_BUFFER_BINDING:
6256 case GL_CURRENT_VERTEX_ATTRIB:
6257 break;
6258
6259 case GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_DIVISOR:
6260 static_assert(
6261 GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_DIVISOR == GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_DIVISOR_ANGLE,
6262 "ANGLE extension enums not equal to GL enums.");
6263 if (context->getClientMajorVersion() < 3 &&
6264 !context->getExtensions().instancedArraysAny())
6265 {
6266 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
6267 return false;
6268 }
6269 break;
6270
6271 case GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_INTEGER:
6272 if (context->getClientMajorVersion() < 3)
6273 {
6274 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
6275 return false;
6276 }
6277 break;
6278
6279 case GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_BINDING:
6280 case GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_RELATIVE_OFFSET:
6281 if (context->getClientVersion() < ES_3_1)
6282 {
6283 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumRequiresGLES31);
6284 return false;
6285 }
6286 break;
6287
6288 default:
6289 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
6290 return false;
6291 }
6292 }
6293
6294 if (length)
6295 {
6296 if (pname == GL_CURRENT_VERTEX_ATTRIB)
6297 {
6298 *length = 4;
6299 }
6300 else

6303 }
6304 }

6306 return true;

6308
6309bool ValidatePixelPack(const Context *context,
6310 GLenum format,
6311 GLenum type,
6312 GLint x,
6313 GLint y,
6314 GLsizei width,
6315 GLsizei height,
6316 GLsizei bufSize,
6317 GLsizei *length,
6318 const void *pixels)
6319{
6320 // Check for pixel pack buffer related API errors
6321 Buffer *pixelPackBuffer = context->getState().getTargetBuffer(BufferBinding::PixelPack);
6322 if (pixelPackBuffer != nullptr && pixelPackBuffer->isMapped())
6323 {
6324 // ...the buffer object's data store is currently mapped.
6325 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBufferMapped);
6326 return false;
6327 }
6328 if (context->getExtensions().webglCompatibility && pixelPackBuffer != nullptr &&
6329 pixelPackBuffer->isBoundForTransformFeedbackAndOtherUse())
6330 {
6331 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kPixelPackBufferBoundForTransformFeedback);
6332 return false;
6333 }
6334
6335 // .. the data would be packed to the buffer object such that the memory writes required
6336 // would exceed the data store size.
6337 const InternalFormat &formatInfo = GetInternalFormatInfo(format, type);
6338 const Extents size(width, height, 1);
6339 const auto &pack = context->getState().getPackState();
6340
6341 GLuint endByte = 0;
6342 if (!formatInfo.computePackUnpackEndByte(type, size, pack, false, &endByte))
6343 {
6344 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kIntegerOverflow);
6345 return false;
6346 }
6347
6348 if (bufSize >= 0)
6349 {
6350 if (pixelPackBuffer == nullptr && static_cast<size_t>(bufSize) < endByte)
6351 {
6352 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInsufficientBufferSize);
6353 return false;
6354 }
6355 }
6356
6357 if (pixelPackBuffer != nullptr)
6358 {
6359 CheckedNumeric<size_t> checkedEndByte(endByte);
6360 CheckedNumeric<size_t> checkedOffset(reinterpret_cast<size_t>(pixels));
6361 checkedEndByte += checkedOffset;
6362
6363 if (checkedEndByte.ValueOrDie() > static_cast<size_t>(pixelPackBuffer->getSize()))
6364 {
6365 // Overflow past the end of the buffer
6366 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kParamOverflow);
6367 return false;
6368 }
6369 }
6370
6371 if (pixelPackBuffer == nullptr && length != nullptr)
6372 {
6373 if (endByte > static_cast<size_t>(std::numeric_limits<GLsizei>::max()))
6374 {
6375 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kIntegerOverflow);
6376 return false;
6377 }
6378
6379 *length = static_cast<GLsizei>(endByte);
6380 }
6381
6382 if (context->getExtensions().webglCompatibility)
6383 {
6384 // WebGL 2.0 disallows the scenario:
6385 // GL_PACK_SKIP_PIXELS + width > DataStoreWidth
6386 // where:
6387 // DataStoreWidth = (GL_PACK_ROW_LENGTH ? GL_PACK_ROW_LENGTH : width)
6388 // Since these two pack parameters can only be set to non-zero values
6389 // on WebGL 2.0 contexts, verify them for all WebGL contexts.
6390 GLint dataStoreWidth = pack.rowLength ? pack.rowLength : width;
6391 if (pack.skipPixels + width > dataStoreWidth)
6392 {
6393 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidPackParametersForWebGL);
6394 return false;
6395 }
6396 }
6397
6398 return true;
6399}
6400
6401bool ValidateReadPixelsBase(const Context *context,
6402 GLint x,
6403 GLint y,
6404 GLsizei width,
6405 GLsizei height,
6406 GLenum format,
6407 GLenum type,
6408 GLsizei bufSize,
6409 GLsizei *length,
6410 GLsizei *columns,
6411 GLsizei *rows,
6412 const void *pixels)
6413{
6414 if (length != nullptr)
6415 {
6416 *length = 0;
6417 }
6418 if (rows != nullptr)
6419 {
6420 *rows = 0;
6421 }
6422 if (columns != nullptr)
6423 {
6424 *columns = 0;
6425 }
6426
6427 if (width < 0 || height < 0)
6428 {
6429 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kNegativeSize);
6430 return false;
6431 }
6432
6433 Framebuffer *readFramebuffer = context->getState().getReadFramebuffer();
6434 ASSERT(readFramebuffer);
6435
6436 if (!ValidateFramebufferComplete(context, readFramebuffer))
6437 {
6438 return false;
6439 }
6440
6441 // needIntrinsic = true. Treat renderToTexture textures as single sample since they will be
6442 // resolved before reading.
6443 if (!readFramebuffer->isDefault() &&
6444 !ValidateFramebufferNotMultisampled(context, readFramebuffer, true))
6445 {
6446 return false;
6447 }
6448
6449 if (readFramebuffer->getReadBufferState() == GL_NONE)
6450 {
6451 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kReadBufferNone);
6452 return false;
6453 }
6454
6455 const FramebufferAttachment *readBuffer = nullptr;
6456 switch (format)
6457 {
6458 case GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT:
6459 readBuffer = readFramebuffer->getDepthAttachment();
6460 break;
6461 case GL_STENCIL_INDEX_OES:
6462 readBuffer = readFramebuffer->getStencilOrDepthStencilAttachment();
6463 break;
6464 default:
6465 readBuffer = readFramebuffer->getReadColorAttachment();
6466 break;
6467 }
6468
6469 // WebGL 1.0 [Section 6.26] Reading From a Missing Attachment
6470 // In OpenGL ES it is undefined what happens when an operation tries to read from a missing
6471 // attachment and WebGL defines it to be an error. We do the check unconditionnaly as the
6472 // situation is an application error that would lead to a crash in ANGLE.
6473 if (readBuffer == nullptr)
6474 {
6475 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kMissingReadAttachment);
6476 return false;
6477 }
6478
6479 // OVR_multiview2, Revision 1:
6480 // ReadPixels generates an INVALID_FRAMEBUFFER_OPERATION error if
6481 // the number of views in the current read framebuffer is more than one.
6482 if (readFramebuffer->readDisallowedByMultiview())
6483 {
6484 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_FRAMEBUFFER_OPERATION, kMultiviewReadFramebuffer);
6485 return false;
6486 }
6487
6488 if (context->getExtensions().webglCompatibility)
6489 {
6490 // The ES 2.0 spec states that the format must be "among those defined in table 3.4,
6491 // excluding formats LUMINANCE and LUMINANCE_ALPHA.". This requires validating the format
6492 // and type before validating the combination of format and type. However, the
6493 // dEQP-GLES3.functional.negative_api.buffer.read_pixels passes GL_LUMINANCE as a format and
6494 // verifies that GL_INVALID_OPERATION is generated.
6495 // TODO(geofflang): Update this check to be done in all/no cases once this is resolved in
6496 // dEQP/WebGL.
6497 if (!ValidReadPixelsFormatEnum(context, format))
6498 {
6499 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidFormat);
6500 return false;
6501 }
6502
6503 if (!ValidReadPixelsTypeEnum(context, type))
6504 {
6505 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidType);
6506 return false;
6507 }
6508 }
6509
6510 GLenum currentFormat = GL_NONE;
6511 GLenum currentType = GL_NONE;
6512
6513 switch (format)
6514 {
6515 case GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT:
6516 case GL_STENCIL_INDEX_OES:
6517 // Only rely on ValidReadPixelsFormatType for depth/stencil formats
6518 break;
6519 default:
6520 currentFormat = readFramebuffer->getImplementationColorReadFormat(context);
6521 currentType = readFramebuffer->getImplementationColorReadType(context);
6522 break;
6523 }
6524
6525 bool validFormatTypeCombination =
6526 ValidReadPixelsFormatType(context, readBuffer->getFormat().info, format, type);
6527
6528 if (!(currentFormat == format && currentType == type) && !validFormatTypeCombination)
6529 {
6530 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kMismatchedTypeAndFormat);
6531 return false;
6532 }
6533
6534 if (!ValidatePixelPack(context, format, type, x, y, width, height, bufSize, length, pixels))
6535 {
6536 return false;
6537 }
6538
6539 auto getClippedExtent = [](GLint start, GLsizei length, int bufferSize, GLsizei *outExtent) {
6540 angle::CheckedNumeric<int> clippedExtent(length);
6541 if (start < 0)
6542 {
6543 // "subtract" the area that is less than 0
6544 clippedExtent += start;
6545 }
6546
6547 angle::CheckedNumeric<int> readExtent = start;
6548 readExtent += length;
6549 if (!readExtent.IsValid())
6550 {
6551 return false;
6552 }
6553
6554 if (readExtent.ValueOrDie() > bufferSize)
6555 {
6556 // Subtract the region to the right of the read buffer
6557 clippedExtent -= (readExtent - bufferSize);
6558 }
6559
6560 if (!clippedExtent.IsValid())
6561 {
6562 return false;
6563 }
6564
6565 *outExtent = std::max(clippedExtent.ValueOrDie(), 0);
6566 return true;
6567 };
6568
6569 GLsizei writtenColumns = 0;
6570 if (!getClippedExtent(x, width, readBuffer->getSize().width, &writtenColumns))
6571 {
6572 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kIntegerOverflow);
6573 return false;
6574 }
6575
6576 GLsizei writtenRows = 0;
6577 if (!getClippedExtent(y, height, readBuffer->getSize().height, &writtenRows))
6578 {
6579 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kIntegerOverflow);
6580 return false;
6581 }
6582
6583 if (columns != nullptr)
6584 {
6585 *columns = writtenColumns;
6586 }
6587
6588 if (rows != nullptr)
6589 {
6590 *rows = writtenRows;
6591 }
6592
6593 return true;
6594}

6596template <typename ParamType>
6597bool ValidateTexParameterBase(const Context *context,
6598 TextureType target,
6599 GLenum pname,
6600 GLsizei bufSize,
6601 bool vectorParams,
6602 const ParamType *params)
6603{
6604 if (!ValidTextureTarget(context, target) && !ValidTextureExternalTarget(context, target))
6605 {
6606 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidTextureTarget);
6607 return false;
6608 }
6609
6610 if (context->getTextureByType(target) == nullptr)
6611 {
6612 // Should only be possible for external textures
6613 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kTextureNotBound);
6614 return false;
6615 }
6616
6617 const GLsizei minBufSize = GetTexParameterCount(pname);
6618 if (bufSize >= 0 && bufSize < minBufSize)
6619 {
6620 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInsufficientBufferSize);
6621 return false;
6622 }
6623
6624 if (context->getClientMajorVersion() == 1 && !IsValidGLES1TextureParameter(pname))
6625 {
6626 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
6627 return false;
6628 }
6629
6630 switch (pname)
6631 {
6632 case GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_R:
6633 case GL_TEXTURE_SWIZZLE_R:
6634 case GL_TEXTURE_SWIZZLE_G:
6635 case GL_TEXTURE_SWIZZLE_B:
6636 case GL_TEXTURE_SWIZZLE_A:
6637 case GL_TEXTURE_BASE_LEVEL:
6638 case GL_TEXTURE_MAX_LEVEL:
6639 case GL_TEXTURE_COMPARE_MODE:
6640 case GL_TEXTURE_COMPARE_FUNC:
6641 case GL_TEXTURE_MIN_LOD:
6642 case GL_TEXTURE_MAX_LOD:
6643 if (context->getClientMajorVersion() < 3 &&
6644 !(pname == GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_R && context->getExtensions().texture3DOES))
6645 {
6646 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kES3Required);
6647 return false;
6648 }
6649 if (target == TextureType::External &&
6650 !context->getExtensions().eglImageExternalEssl3OES)
6651 {
6652 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
6653 return false;
6654 }
6655 if (target == TextureType::VideoImage && !context->getExtensions().webglVideoTexture)
6656 {
6657 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
6658 }
6659 break;
6660
6661 case GL_GENERATE_MIPMAP:
6662 case GL_TEXTURE_CROP_RECT_OES:
6663 if (context->getClientMajorVersion() > 1)
6664 {
6665 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kGLES1Only);
6666 return false;
6667 }
6668 break;
6669
6670 default:
6671 break;
6672 }
6673
6674 if (target == TextureType::_2DMultisample || target == TextureType::_2DMultisampleArray)
6675 {
6676 switch (pname)
6677 {
6678 case GL_TEXTURE_MIN_FILTER:
6679 case GL_TEXTURE_MAG_FILTER:
6680 case GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_S:
6681 case GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_T:
6682 case GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_R:
6683 case GL_TEXTURE_MIN_LOD:
6684 case GL_TEXTURE_MAX_LOD:
6685 case GL_TEXTURE_COMPARE_MODE:
6686 case GL_TEXTURE_COMPARE_FUNC:
6687 case GL_TEXTURE_BORDER_COLOR:
6688 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidPname);
6689 return false;
6690 }
6691 }
6692
6693 switch (pname)
6694 {
6695 case GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_S:
6696 case GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_T:
6697 case GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_R:
6698 {
6699 bool restrictedWrapModes = ((target == TextureType::External &&
6700 !context->getExtensions().eglImageExternalWrapModesEXT) ||
6701 target == TextureType::Rectangle);
6702 if (!ValidateTextureWrapModeValue(context, params, restrictedWrapModes))
6703 {
6704 return false;
6705 }
6706 }
6707 break;
6708
6709 case GL_TEXTURE_MIN_FILTER:
6710 {
6711 bool restrictedMinFilter =
6712 target == TextureType::External || target == TextureType::Rectangle;
6713 if (!ValidateTextureMinFilterValue(context, params, restrictedMinFilter))
6714 {
6715 return false;
6716 }
6717 }
6718 break;
6719
6720 case GL_TEXTURE_MAG_FILTER:
6721 if (!ValidateTextureMagFilterValue(context, params))
6722 {
6723 return false;
6724 }
6725 break;
6726
6727 case GL_TEXTURE_USAGE_ANGLE:
6728 if (!context->getExtensions().textureUsage)
6729 {
6730 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
6731 return false;
6732 }
6733
6734 switch (ConvertToGLenum(params[0]))
6735 {
6736 case GL_NONE:
6737 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_ANGLE:
6738 break;
6739
6740 default:
6741 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
6742 return false;
6743 }
6744 break;
6745
6746 case GL_TEXTURE_MAX_ANISOTROPY_EXT:
6747 {
6748 GLfloat paramValue = static_cast<GLfloat>(params[0]);
6749 if (!ValidateTextureMaxAnisotropyValue(context, paramValue))
6750 {
6751 return false;
6752 }
6753 ASSERT(static_cast<ParamType>(paramValue) == params[0]);
6754 }
6755 break;
6756
6757 case GL_TEXTURE_MIN_LOD:
6758 case GL_TEXTURE_MAX_LOD:
6759 // any value is permissible
6760 break;
6761
6762 case GL_TEXTURE_COMPARE_MODE:
6763 if (!ValidateTextureCompareModeValue(context, params))
6764 {
6765 return false;
6766 }
6767 break;
6768
6769 case GL_TEXTURE_COMPARE_FUNC:
6770 if (!ValidateTextureCompareFuncValue(context, params))
6771 {
6772 return false;
6773 }
6774 break;
6775
6776 case GL_TEXTURE_SWIZZLE_R:
6777 case GL_TEXTURE_SWIZZLE_G:
6778 case GL_TEXTURE_SWIZZLE_B:
6779 case GL_TEXTURE_SWIZZLE_A:
6780 switch (ConvertToGLenum(params[0]))
6781 {
6782 case GL_RED:
6783 case GL_GREEN:
6784 case GL_BLUE:
6785 case GL_ALPHA:
6786 case GL_ZERO:
6787 case GL_ONE:
6788 break;
6789
6790 default:
6791 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
6792 return false;
6793 }
6794 break;
6795
6796 case GL_TEXTURE_BASE_LEVEL:
6797 if (ConvertToGLint(params[0]) < 0)
6798 {
6799 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kBaseLevelNegative);
6800 return false;
6801 }
6802 if (target == TextureType::External && static_cast<GLuint>(params[0]) != 0)
6803 {
6804 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBaseLevelNonZero);
6805 return false;
6806 }
6807 if ((target == TextureType::_2DMultisample ||
6808 target == TextureType::_2DMultisampleArray) &&
6809 static_cast<GLuint>(params[0]) != 0)
6810 {
6811 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBaseLevelNonZero);
6812 return false;
6813 }
6814 if (target == TextureType::Rectangle && static_cast<GLuint>(params[0]) != 0)
6815 {
6816 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBaseLevelNonZero);
6817 return false;
6818 }
6819 break;
6820
6821 case GL_TEXTURE_MAX_LEVEL:
6822 if (ConvertToGLint(params[0]) < 0)
6823 {
6824 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidMipLevel);
6825 return false;
6826 }
6827 break;
6828
6829 case GL_DEPTH_STENCIL_TEXTURE_MODE:
6830 if (context->getClientVersion() < Version(3, 1))
6831 {
6832 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumRequiresGLES31);
6833 return false;
6834 }
6835 switch (ConvertToGLenum(params[0]))
6836 {
6837 case GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT:
6838 case GL_STENCIL_INDEX:
6839 break;
6840
6841 default:
6842 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
6843 return false;
6844 }
6845 break;
6846
6847 case GL_TEXTURE_SRGB_DECODE_EXT:
6848 if (!ValidateTextureSRGBDecodeValue(context, params))
6849 {
6850 return false;
6851 }
6852 break;
6853
6854 case GL_TEXTURE_FORMAT_SRGB_OVERRIDE_EXT:
6855 if (!ValidateTextureSRGBOverrideValue(context, params))
6856 {
6857 return false;
6858 }
6859 break;
6860
6861 case GL_GENERATE_MIPMAP:
6862 if (context->getClientMajorVersion() > 1)
6863 {
6864 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kGLES1Only);
6865 return false;
6866 }
6867 break;
6868
6869 case GL_TEXTURE_CROP_RECT_OES:
6870 if (context->getClientMajorVersion() > 1)
6871 {
6872 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kGLES1Only);
6873 return false;
6874 }
6875 if (!vectorParams)
6876 {
6877 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInsufficientBufferSize);
6878 return false;
6879 }
6880 break;
6881
6882 case GL_TEXTURE_BORDER_COLOR:
6883 if (!context->getExtensions().textureBorderClampOES)
6884 {
6885 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kExtensionNotEnabled);
6886 return false;
6887 }
6888 if (!vectorParams)
6889 {
6890 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInsufficientBufferSize);
6891 return false;
6892 }
6893 break;
6894
6895 case GL_RESOURCE_INITIALIZED_ANGLE:
6896 if (!context->getExtensions().robustResourceInitialization)
6897 {
6898 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM,
6899 kRobustResourceInitializationExtensionRequired);
6900 return false;
6901 }
6902
6903 break;
6904
6905 default:
6906 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
6907 return false;
6908 }
6909
6910 return true;
6911}

6943bool ValidateGetActiveUniformBlockivBase(const Context *context,
6944 ShaderProgramID program,
6945 GLuint uniformBlockIndex,
6946 GLenum pname,
6947 GLsizei *length)
6948{
6949 if (length)
6950 {
6951 *length = 0;
6952 }
6953
6954 if (context->getClientMajorVersion() < 3)
6955 {
6956 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kES3Required);
6957 return false;
6958 }
6959
6960 Program *programObject = GetValidProgram(context, program);
6961 if (!programObject)
6962 {
6963 return false;
6964 }
6965
6966 if (uniformBlockIndex >= programObject->getActiveUniformBlockCount())
6967 {
6968 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kIndexExceedsActiveUniformBlockCount);
6969 return false;
6970 }
6971
6972 switch (pname)
6973 {
6974 case GL_UNIFORM_BLOCK_BINDING:
6975 case GL_UNIFORM_BLOCK_DATA_SIZE:
6976 case GL_UNIFORM_BLOCK_NAME_LENGTH:
6977 case GL_UNIFORM_BLOCK_ACTIVE_UNIFORMS:
6978 case GL_UNIFORM_BLOCK_ACTIVE_UNIFORM_INDICES:
6979 case GL_UNIFORM_BLOCK_REFERENCED_BY_VERTEX_SHADER:
6980 case GL_UNIFORM_BLOCK_REFERENCED_BY_FRAGMENT_SHADER:
6981 break;
6982
6983 default:
6984 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
6985 return false;
6986 }
6987
6988 if (length)
6989 {
6990 if (pname == GL_UNIFORM_BLOCK_ACTIVE_UNIFORM_INDICES)
6991 {
6992 const InterfaceBlock &uniformBlock =
6993 programObject->getUniformBlockByIndex(uniformBlockIndex);
6994 *length = static_cast<GLsizei>(uniformBlock.memberIndexes.size());
6995 }
6996 else
6997 {
6998 *length = 1;
6999 }
7000 }
7001
7002 return true;

7005template <typename ParamType>
7006bool ValidateSamplerParameterBase(const Context *context,
7007 SamplerID sampler,
7008 GLenum pname,
7009 GLsizei bufSize,
7010 bool vectorParams,
7011 const ParamType *params)
7012{
7013 if (context->getClientMajorVersion() < 3)
7014 {
7015 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kES3Required);
7016 return false;
7017 }
7018
7019 if (!context->isSampler(sampler))
7020 {
7021 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidSampler);
7022 return false;
7023 }
7024
7025 const GLsizei minBufSize = GetSamplerParameterCount(pname);
7026 if (bufSize >= 0 && bufSize < minBufSize)
7027 {
7028 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInsufficientBufferSize);
7029 return false;
7030 }
7031
7032 switch (pname)
7033 {
7034 case GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_S:
7035 case GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_T:
7036 case GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_R:
7037 if (!ValidateTextureWrapModeValue(context, params, false))
7038 {
7039 return false;
7040 }
7041 break;
7042
7043 case GL_TEXTURE_MIN_FILTER:
7044 if (!ValidateTextureMinFilterValue(context, params, false))
7045 {
7046 return false;
7047 }
7048 break;
7049
7050 case GL_TEXTURE_MAG_FILTER:
7051 if (!ValidateTextureMagFilterValue(context, params))
7052 {
7053 return false;
7054 }
7055 break;
7056
7057 case GL_TEXTURE_MIN_LOD:
7058 case GL_TEXTURE_MAX_LOD:
7059 // any value is permissible
7060 break;
7061
7062 case GL_TEXTURE_COMPARE_MODE:
7063 if (!ValidateTextureCompareModeValue(context, params))
7064 {
7065 return false;
7066 }
7067 break;
7068
7069 case GL_TEXTURE_COMPARE_FUNC:
7070 if (!ValidateTextureCompareFuncValue(context, params))
7071 {
7072 return false;
7073 }
7074 break;
7075
7076 case GL_TEXTURE_SRGB_DECODE_EXT:
7077 if (!ValidateTextureSRGBDecodeValue(context, params))
7078 {
7079 return false;
7080 }
7081 break;
7082
7083 case GL_TEXTURE_MAX_ANISOTROPY_EXT:
7084 {
7085 GLfloat paramValue = static_cast<GLfloat>(params[0]);
7086 if (!ValidateTextureMaxAnisotropyValue(context, paramValue))
7087 {
7088 return false;
7089 }
7090 }
7091 break;
7092
7093 case GL_TEXTURE_BORDER_COLOR:
7094 if (!context->getExtensions().textureBorderClampOES)
7095 {
7096 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kExtensionNotEnabled);
7097 return false;
7098 }
7099 if (!vectorParams)
7100 {
7101 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInsufficientBufferSize);
7102 return false;
7103 }
7104 break;
7105
7106 default:
7107 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
7108 return false;
7109 }
7110
7111 return true;
7112}

7203bool ValidateGetInternalFormativBase(const Context *context,
7204 GLenum target,
7205 GLenum internalformat,
7206 GLenum pname,
7207 GLsizei bufSize,
7208 GLsizei *numParams)
7209{
7210 if (numParams)
7211 {
7212 *numParams = 0;
7213 }
7214
7215 if (context->getClientMajorVersion() < 3)
7216 {
7217 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kES3Required);
7218 return false;
7219 }
7220
7221 const TextureCaps &formatCaps = context->getTextureCaps().get(internalformat);
7222 if (!formatCaps.renderbuffer)
7223 {
7224 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kFormatNotRenderable);
7225 return false;
7226 }
7227
7228 switch (target)
7229 {
7230 case GL_RENDERBUFFER:
7231 break;
7232
7233 case GL_TEXTURE_2D_MULTISAMPLE:
7234 if (context->getClientVersion() < ES_3_1 &&
7235 !context->getExtensions().textureMultisample)
7236 {
7237 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM,
7238 kMultisampleTextureExtensionOrES31Required);
7239 return false;
7240 }
7241 break;
7242 case GL_TEXTURE_2D_MULTISAMPLE_ARRAY_OES:
7243 if (!context->getExtensions().textureStorageMultisample2DArrayOES)
7244 {
7245 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kMultisampleArrayExtensionRequired);
7246 return false;
7247 }
7248 break;
7249 default:
7250 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidTarget);
7251 return false;
7252 }
7253
7254 if (bufSize < 0)
7255 {
7256 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInsufficientBufferSize);
7257 return false;
7258 }
7259
7260 GLsizei maxWriteParams = 0;
7261 switch (pname)
7262 {
7263 case GL_NUM_SAMPLE_COUNTS:
7264 maxWriteParams = 1;
7265 break;
7266
7267 case GL_SAMPLES:
7268 maxWriteParams = static_cast<GLsizei>(formatCaps.sampleCounts.size());
7269 break;
7270
7271 default:
7272 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
7273 return false;
7274 }
7275
7276 if (numParams)
7277 {
7278 // glGetInternalFormativ will not overflow bufSize
7279 *numParams = std::min(bufSize, maxWriteParams);
7280 }
7281
7282 return true;
7283}

7310bool ValidateTexStorageMultisample(const Context *context,
7311 TextureType target,
7312 GLsizei samples,
7313 GLint internalFormat,
7314 GLsizei width,
7315 GLsizei height)
7316{
7317 const Caps &caps = context->getCaps();
7318 if (width > caps.max2DTextureSize || height > caps.max2DTextureSize)
7319 {
7320 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kTextureWidthOrHeightOutOfRange);
7321 return false;
7322 }
7323
7324 if (samples == 0)
7325 {
7326 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kSamplesZero);
7327 return false;
7328 }
7329
7330 const TextureCaps &formatCaps = context->getTextureCaps().get(internalFormat);
7331 if (!formatCaps.textureAttachment)
7332 {
7333 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kRenderableInternalFormat);
7334 return false;
7335 }
7336
7337 // The ES3.1 spec(section 8.8) states that an INVALID_ENUM error is generated if internalformat
7338 // is one of the unsized base internalformats listed in table 8.11.
7339 const InternalFormat &formatInfo = GetSizedInternalFormatInfo(internalFormat);
7340 if (formatInfo.internalFormat == GL_NONE)
7341 {
7342 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kUnsizedInternalFormatUnsupported);
7343 return false;
7344 }
7345
7346 if (static_cast<GLuint>(samples) > formatCaps.getMaxSamples())
7347 {
7348 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kSamplesOutOfRange);
7349 return false;
7350 }
7351
7352 Texture *texture = context->getTextureByType(target);
7353 if (!texture || texture->id().value == 0)
7354 {
7355 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kZeroBoundToTarget);
7356 return false;
7357 }
7358
7359 if (texture->getImmutableFormat())
7360 {
7361 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kImmutableTextureBound);
7362 return false;
7363 }
7364 return true;
7365}

7389bool ValidateGetTexLevelParameterBase(const Context *context,
7390 TextureTarget target,
7391 GLint level,
7392 GLenum pname,
7393 GLsizei *length)
7394{
7395
7396 if (length)
7397 {
7398 *length = 0;
7399 }
7400
7401 TextureType type = TextureTargetToType(target);
7402
7403 if (!ValidTexLevelDestinationTarget(context, type))
7404 {

7407 }
7408

7410 {
7411 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kTextureNotBound);
7412 return false;
7413 }
7414
7415 if (!ValidMipLevel(context, type, level))
7416 {
7417 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidMipLevel);
7418 return false;

7420

7424 case GL_TEXTURE_GREEN_TYPE:

7430 case GL_TEXTURE_BLUE_SIZE:
7431 case GL_TEXTURE_ALPHA_SIZE:
7432 case GL_TEXTURE_DEPTH_SIZE:
7433 case GL_TEXTURE_STENCIL_SIZE:
7434 case GL_TEXTURE_SHARED_SIZE:

7436 case GL_TEXTURE_WIDTH:

7439 case GL_TEXTURE_SAMPLES:

7451 break;
7452
7453 case GL_TEXTURE_BUFFER_DATA_STORE_BINDING:
7454 case GL_TEXTURE_BUFFER_OFFSET:
7455 case GL_TEXTURE_BUFFER_SIZE:
7456 if (context->getClientVersion() < Version(3, 2) &&
7457 !context->getExtensions().textureBufferAny())
7458 {
7459 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kTextureBufferExtensionNotAvailable);
7460 return false;

7462 break;
7463
7464 default:
7465 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidPname);

7510void RecordDrawAttribsError(const Context *context)
7511{
7512 // An overflow can happen when adding the offset. Check against a special constant.
7513 if (context->getStateCache().getNonInstancedVertexElementLimit() ==
7514 VertexAttribute::kIntegerOverflow ||
7515 context->getStateCache().getInstancedVertexElementLimit() ==
7516 VertexAttribute::kIntegerOverflow)
7517 {
7518 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kIntegerOverflow);
7519 }
7520 else
7521 {
7522 // [OpenGL ES 3.0.2] section 2.9.4 page 40:
7523 // We can return INVALID_OPERATION if our buffer does not have enough backing data.
7524 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInsufficientVertexBufferSize);
7525 }
7526}

7542 case GraphicsResetStatus::UnknownContextReset:

7552 case GraphicsResetStatus::InnocentContextReset:
7553 case GraphicsResetStatus::UnknownContextReset:
7554 break;

7556 default:
7557 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidResetStatus);
